mpile check (no agent CLI needed)\\n    15→```\\n    16→\\n    17→**Do NOT run E2E tests proactively.** They make real API calls that consume tokens and cost money. Only run when explicitly asked.\\n    18→\\n    19→## Structure\\n    20→\\n    21→```\\n    22→e2e/\\n    23→├── agents/       # Agent abstraction (Agent interface, tmux sessions, concurrency gates)\\n    24→├── bootstrap/    # CI pre-test setup (auth config, warmup)\\n    25→├── entire/       # `entire` CLI wrapper (enable, rewind, etc.)\\n    26→├── exploratory/  # Experimental tests, not run by CI\\n    27→├── tests/        # Blessed test files (run by CI)\\n    28→└── testutil/     # Repo setup, assertions, artifact capture\\n    29→```\\n    30→\\n    31→## Key Patterns\\n    32→\\n    33→- Every test uses `testutil.ForEachAgent` which runs it per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling.\\n    34→- All operations go through `RepoState` (`s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`) so they're logged to `console.log`.\\n    35→- Use the `entire` package for CLI interactions, not raw `exec.Command`.\\n    36→- Skip tests pending CLI fixes with `t.Skip(\\\"ENT-XXX: reason\\\")`.\\n    37→\\n    38→## Adding a New Agent\\n    39→\\n    40→1. Create `agents/<name>.go` implementing the `Agent` interface.\\n    41→2. Register it in `init()` with `Register(&YourAgent{})`.\\n    42→3. Add a `Bootstrap()` method for any CI-specific setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    43→4. Add a `RegisterGate(\\\"<name>\\\", N)` call if concurrency needs limiting.\\n    44→5. Ensure the agent name is accepted by `mise run test:e2e --agent <name>`.\\n    45→6. Add the agent to `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` matrix and `e2e-isolated.yml` options.\\n    46→\\n    47→## Environment Variables\\n    48→\\n    49→| Variable | Description | Default |\\n    50→|----------|-------------|---------|\\n    51→| `E2E_AGENT` | Agent to test (`claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`, `cursor-cli`, `copilot-cli`) | all registered |\\n    52→| `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` | Path to a pre-built `entire` binary | builds from source |\\n    53→| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Timeout per prompt | `2m` |\\n    54→| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Set to `1` to preserve temp repos after test | unset |\\n    55→| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output directory | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n    56→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n    57→| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n    58→| `COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN` | Required for Copilot CLI (or `gh auth login`) | — |\\n    59→\\n    60→## Debugging Failures\\n    61→\\n    62→Artifacts are captured to `e2e/artifacts/` on every run (git-log, git-tree, console.log, checkpoint metadata, entire logs). Set `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1` to preserve the temp repo — a symlink appears in the artifact dir pointing to it.\\n    63→\\n    64→Use the `debug-e2e` skill (`.claude/skills/debug-e2e/`) for a structured workflow when investigating failures.\\n    65→\\n    66→### Reading artifacts\\n    67→\\n    68→- `console.log` — full operation transcript including agent stdout/stderr\\n    69→- `git-log.txt` — commit history at time of failure\\n    70→- `git-tree.txt` — working tree state\\n    71→- `entire-logs/` — internal CLI logs\\n    72→\\n    73→### Fixing flaky tests\\n    74→\\n    75→When a test passes on retry but failed once, the problem is usually agent non-determinism, not a CLI bug. Common patterns:\\n    76→\\n    77→- **Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting**: The model output contains \\\"Does this look right?\\\" or \\\"Should I proceed?\\\". Fix: append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\" to the prompt.\\n    78→- **Agent wrote to wrong path or created extra files**: Fix: be more explicit about exact file paths and what _not_ to do.\\n    79→- **Agent committed when it shouldn't have**: Fix: add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to the prompt.\\n    80→- **Checkpoint wait timeout**: `WaitForCheckpoint` or `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom` exceeded deadline. Fix: increase the timeout argument.\\n    81→\\n    82→To diagnose: read `console.log` in the failing test's artifact directory. Compare what the agent actually did vs what the test expected.\\n    83→\\n    84→## CI Workflows\\n    85→\\n    86→- **`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** — Runs full suite on push to main. Matrix: `[claude-code, opencode, gemini-cli, cursor-cli, copilot-cli]`.\\n    87→- **`.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml`** — Manual dispatch for debugging a single test. Inputs: agent + test name filter.\\n    88→\\n    89→Both workflows run `go run ./e2e/bootstrap` before tests to handle agent-specific CI setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    90→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"3ef29242-db49-445b-8e3d-75027b26f7da\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T13:34:08.657Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a0db8b7180da30f89\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_019wBA7esv8bw9EJUHxBZ8H2\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01DUfJ49oqTPmjrow1P5kikF\",\"uuid\":\"d279d348-e5be-45c6-91c9-fd8c40b680da\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T13:34:08.658Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/e2e-with-git-remote\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d279d348-e5be-45c6-91c9-fd8c40b680da\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T13:34:10.760Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01LEnRXkHd1n9JkcsheK9vou\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01QSg63Rm4yEtmtSTTWgXbn7\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"find /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1 -type f -name \\\"*test.go\\\" | xargs grep -l \\\"push\\\\|Pull\\\\|fetch\\\\|remote\\\\|PrePush\\\\|pre-push\\\\|SetupBare\\\\|clone\\\" | sort\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason