led: %v\\\", err)\\n    }\\n    \\n    // 2. User commits\\n    s.Git(t, \\\"add\\\", \\\".\\\")\\n    s.Git(t, \\\"commit\\\", \\\"-m\\\", \\\"Add md file about red\\\")\\n    \\n    // 3. Wait for async post-commit hook\\n    testutil.WaitForCheckpoint(t, s, 15*time.Second)\\n    \\n    // 4. Assert outcomes\\n    testutil.AssertCheckpointAdvanced(t, s)\\n    cpID := testutil.AssertHasCheckpointTrailer(t, s.Dir, \\\"HEAD\\\")\\n    testutil.AssertCheckpointExists(t, s.Dir, cpID)\\n    testutil.AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete(t, s.Dir, cpID)\\n    testutil.AssertNoShadowBranches(t, s.Dir)\\n})\\n```\\n\\n**Key Pattern Elements:**\\n\\n1. **ForEachAgent wrapper:** Runs test for each registered agent (claude-code, gemini-cli, opencode, cursor-cli, copilot-cli)\\n   - Handles repo setup, concurrency gating, timeout scaling\\n   - Auto-restarts scenario on transient API errors (max 3 attempts)\\n   - Captures artifacts on failure (console.log, git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, entire-logs/)\\n\\n2. **RepoState object:** Central test state holder\\n   - `.Dir` - temp repo directory\\n   - `.Agent` - Agent interface\\n   - `.HeadBefore` / `.CheckpointBefore` - baseline refs for assertions\\n   - `.ConsoleLog` - incrementally written transcript\\n   - Provides `.RunPrompt()`, `.Git()`, `.StartSession()` helpers\\n\\n3. **Async wait pattern:** Post-commit hooks are async\\n   - Use `WaitForCheckpoint(timeout)` before assertions\\n   - Use `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom(fromRef, timeout)` for subsequent checkpoints\\n   - Use `WaitForSessionIdle(timeout)` for turn-end transitions\\n\\n4. **Assertion helpers:** Pre-built for common scenarios\\n   - `AssertFileExists()`, `WaitForFileExists()` - file creation\\n   - `AssertNewCommits()` - commit count verification\\n   - `AssertCheckpointAdvanced()` - checkpoint branch moved\\n   - `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete()` - all fields populated\\n   - `AssertNoShadowBranches()` - cleanup verification\\n   - `WaitForCheckpoint()` / `WaitF