` - commit count verification\\n   - `AssertCheckpointAdvanced()` - checkpoint branch moved\\n   - `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete()` - all fields populated\\n   - `AssertNoShadowBranches()` - cleanup verification\\n   - `WaitForCheckpoint()` / `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom()` - async race handling\\n\\n5. **Metadata validation helpers:**\\n   - `CheckpointIDs()` - list all checkpoint IDs from metadata branch tree\\n   - `ReadCheckpointMetadata()` - parse checkpoint-level metadata.json\\n   - `ReadSessionMetadata()` - parse session-level metadata.json\\n   - `WaitForSessionMetadata()` - poll until available\\n   - `GetCheckpointTrailer()` - extract Entire-Checkpoint trailer from commit\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. **E2E Testutil Helpers - Critical for Remote Tests**\\n\\n**Key helper in `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/e2e/testutil/repo.go`:**\\n\\n**SetupBareRemote** (lines 575-596):\\n```go\\n// SetupBareRemote creates a bare git repo, adds it as \\\"origin\\\", and pushes\\n// the initial commit. Returns the bare repo path.\\nfunc SetupBareRemote(t *testing.T, s *RepoState) string {\\n    var bareDir string\\n    if os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_KEEP_REPOS\\\") != \\\"\\\" {\\n        bareDir, err = os.MkdirTemp(\\\"\\\", \\\"e2e-bare-*\\\")\\n        // preserved for inspection\\n    } else {\\n        bareDir = t.TempDir()\\n    }\\n    \\n    Git(t, bareDir, \\\"init\\\", \\\"--bare\\\")\\n    Git(t, s.Dir, \\\"remote\\\", \\\"add\\\", \\\"origin\\\", bareDir)\\n    Git(t, s.Dir, \\\"push\\\", \\\"-u\\\", \\\"origin\\\", \\\"HEAD\\\")\\n    return bareDir\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Other critical helpers:**\\n- `Git(t, dir, args...)` - run git command, fail on error\\n- `GitOutput(t, dir, args...)` - run git, return trimmed stdout\\n- `GitOutputErr(dir, args...)` - non-failing variant\\n- `NewCheckpointCommits(t, s)` - SHAs of new commits on entire/checkpoints/v1 since setup\\n- `PatchSettings(t, dir, extra map[string]any)` - merge keys into .entire/settings.json\\n- `s.ConsoleLog` - File handle for incrementally writing test transcript\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. **Integration Test Structure**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/`\\n\\n**38 test files covering:**\\n- Phase transitions, session lifecycle, rewind, deferred finalization\\n- Carry-forward, overlap detection, content-aware checks\\n- Git author, subdirectory handling, mid-session operations\\n- Workflow, attribution, hooks\\n\\n**Key Infrastructure (`testenv.go`, 200+ lines):**\\n\\n```go\\ntype TestEnv struct {\\n    T                  *testing.T\\n    RepoDir            string\\n    ClaudeProjectDir   string\\n    GeminiProjectDir   string\\n    OpenCodeProjectDir string\\n    SessionCounter     int\\n}\\n\\n// Helpers:\\nenv := NewFeatureBranchEnv(t)  // Init + feature branch (common setup)\\nenv.InitRepo()                 // git init + config\\nenv.InitEntire()               // entire enable\\nenv.WriteFile(path, content)   // Create file\\nenv.GitAdd(path)               // git add\\nenv.GitCommit(msg)             // git commit\\nenv.GitCheckoutNewBranch(name) // git checkout -b\\nenv.RunCLI(args...)            // Execute entire CLI\\nenv.RunCLIWithError(args...)   // CLI with error handling\\nenv.RunCLIWithStdin(stdin, args...)  // CLI with stdin\\n\\n// Query helpers:\\nenv.GetHeadHash()              // Current HEAD SHA\\nenv.GetRef(refName)            // Get any ref SHA\\n```\\n\\n**Test Pattern from `manual_commit_workflow_test.go`:**\\n\\nThe file is 74.7KB (large, comprehensive workflow simulation):\\n- Phase 1: Setup repo with commits\\n- Phase 2-8: Sequential session operations with hook invocation\\n- Verification at each step (checkpoint creation, tree building, rewind points)\\n- Shows full checkpoint lifecycle: shadow branch → condensation → metadata branch\\n\\n**Integration vs E2E:**\\n- **Integration tests:** Fast, no API calls, use testutil helpers, test hooks/strategy directly\\n- **E2E tests:** Slower, real agent calls, use agents library, test full CLI flow\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. **Push Implementation Details**\\n\\n**Push Flow (`push_common.go`, 314 lines + `manual_commit_push.go`, 41 lines):**\\n\\n**PrePush Hook** (`manual_commit_push.go`):\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrePush(ctx context.Context, remote string) error {\\n    // Load settings once for both remote resolution and push_sessions check\\n    ps := resolvePushSettings(ctx, remote)\\n    \\n    // Push entire/checkpoints/v1 to checkpoint URL (if configured)\\n    // or to push remote\\n    if !ps.pushDisabled {\\n        err := pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.pushTarget(), \\n            paths.MetadataBranchName)\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Trails always go to user's push remote\\n    err := pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.remote, paths.TrailsBranchName)\\n    return err\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key Functions:**\\n1. `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, target, branchName)` - Check if branch has unpushed changes, push if needed\\n   - Target can be remote name (\\\"origin\\\") or URL for direct push\\n   - Skips push for URLs (no remote-tracking refs, git handles no-op)\\n\\n2. `doPushBranch(ctx, target, branchName)` - Push with recovery\\n   - Try push first\\n   - On non-fast-forward: fetch + merge\\n   - Retry push after merge\\n   - Gracefully warn on failure (non-fatal)\\n\\n3. `hasUnpushedSessionsCommon(repo, remote, localHash, branchName)` - Compare local vs remote\\n   - Remote tracking ref: `refs/remotes/<remote>/<branch>`\\n   - Returns true if any difference\\n\\n4. `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon(ctx, target, branchName)` - Handle remote conflicts\\n   - Fetch to temp ref (for URLs) or remote-tracking ref\\n   - Reconcile disconnected metadata branch (empty-orphan bug fix)\\n   - Flatten both trees (session logs have unique `cond-*` dirs, no conflicts)\\n   - Create merge commit with both parents\\n   - Updates local branch ref\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **Checkpoint Remote Implementation**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go` (323 lines)\\n\\n**Key Components:**\\n\\n1. **URL Derivation:**\\n   - Parse push remote URL (SSH SCP, HTTPS, or `ssh://` formats)\\n   - Extract: protocol, host, owner, repo\\n   - Derive checkpoint URL using same protocol as push remote\\n   - Example: if push remote is `git@github.com:org/repo.git` → `git@github.com:org/checkpoints.git`\\n\\n2. **Fork Detection:**\\n   - Compare push remote owner vs checkpoint remote owner\\n   - Skip if different (user has forked the repo)\\n\\n3. **Fetch on First Push:**\\n   - `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing()` called once\\n   - Checks if `entire/checkpoints/v1` exists locally\\n   - If missing, fetches from checkpoint URL (30s timeout)\\n   - Failure is silent (push will create branch on remote)\\n   - Once branch exists locally, future pushes skip fetch entirely\\n\\n4. **resolvePushSettings()** (key function, lines 55-133):\\n   - Loads `.entire/settings.json` once\\n   - Resolves checkpoint_remote config: `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}`\\n   - Gets push remote URL\\n   - Parses for protocol detection\\n   - Derives checkpoint URL or returns remote name\\n   - One-time metadata branch fetch if missing\\n   - Returns `pushSettings` struct with `remote`, `checkpointURL`, `pushDisabled`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. **Pre-Push Hook Handler**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_git_cmd.go` (lines 192-214)\\n\\n```go\\nfunc newHooksGitPrePushCmd() *cobra.Command {\\n    return &cobra.Command{\\n        Use:   \\\"pre-push <remote>\\\",\\n        Short: \\\"Handle pre-push git hook\\\",\\n        Args:  cobra.ExactArgs(1),\\n        RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\\n            if gitHooksDisabled {\\n                return nil  // Entire not enabled\\n            }\\n            \\n            g := newGitHookContext(cmd.Context(), \\\"pre-push\\\")\\n            defer g.span.End()\\n            g.logInvoked(slog.String(\\\"remote\\\", args[0]))\\n            \\n            hookErr := g.strategy.PrePush(g.ctx, args[0])\\n            g.logCompleted(hookErr)\\n            return nil\\n        },\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Hook Context:**\\n- Logging initialized via `logging.Init()` \\n- Perf span created for timing breakdown\\n- Strategy method `PrePush(ctx, remote)` invoked\\n- Errors recorded on span\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. **Vogon Agent (E2E Canary)**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/e2e/vogon/main.go` (300+ lines)\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n- Deterministic fake agent for canary (zero-cost) E2E tests\\n- No API calls, no tokens\\n- Parses prompts via regex to determine file operations\\n- Fires lifecycle hooks: `session-start`, `user-prompt-submit`, `stop`, `session-end`\\n\\n**Supported operations** (parsed from prompt text):\\n- `create a [markdown|text] file [at|called] <path>` → create file\\n- `create N files: <path> about <topic>, ...` → multi-file creation\\n- `modify <path>` → append \\\"// Modified by vogon agent\\\\n\\\"\\n- `modify N files: src/model.go should ...` → multi-file modify\\n- `delete <path>` → delete file\\n- `commit` → `git add && git commit` (unless \\\"do not commit\\\" in prompt)\\n- `commit each file separately` → interleave creates with commits\\n- Numbered steps: `(1) Create A. (2) Commit. (3) Create B.` → preserve ordering\\n- Inline content: `with content 'package main; func Foo() {}'` → verbatim content\\n\\n**Critical Note for Test Prompt Wording:**\\n- Vogon parses prompts with hardcoded regexes\\n- When changing E2E test prompt text, **must run `mise run test:e2e:canary`**\\n- If canary fails after prompt change, update Vogon's parsing regexes in `e2e/vogon/main.go`\\n- Example patterns fail if wordings change:\\n  - \\\"create a markdown file at X\\\" vs \\\"create markdown file X\\\" (both match, but different subgroup positions)\\n  - \\\"git 