nch\":\"soph/e2e-with-git-remote\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b635e819-a961-49de-aae2-4956782c1c83\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01XMpBLAuRgkpHQBPLEusDUA\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01XMpBLAuRgkpHQBPLEusDUA\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T14:27:50.262Z\",\"uuid\":\"bf29c574-fa7b-4b87-8504-9a5e61ca025e\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/e2e-with-git-remote\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e89d7b3f-3ab6-4dcc-baef-e61b9f7d963a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"promptId\":\"7582a44a-f3ae-48db-9987-80bfed878af3\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XMpBLAuRgkpHQBPLEusDUA\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary based on all the files I've read. Let me compile the findings:\\n\\n## Summary of Implementation Details: E2E Testing for Remote Git Operations\\n\\nBased on my thorough code analysis, here are the exact implementation details you need for accurate test requirements:\\n\\n### 1. **Push Common Flow** (`push_common.go`)\\n\\n**Key Functions & Signatures:**\\n\\n- **`pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, target, branchName)`**: Pushes a branch to a remote/URL if it has unpushed changes\\n  - `target` can be: remote name (e.g., \\\"origin\\\") OR direct URL (e.g., \\\"https://github.com/org/repo.git\\\")\\n  - Skips \\\"has unpushed\\\" optimization when target is a URL (no remote tracking refs exist)\\n  - Returns `nil` on success; silently returns nil on failure (hooks must not fail)\\n\\n- **`hasUnpushedSessionsCommon(repo, remote, localHash, branchName)`**: Checks if branch differs from remote\\n  - Looks for `refs/remotes/<remote>/<branch>` tracking ref\\n  - Returns `true` if tracking ref missing OR hashes differ\\n  - Returns `false` only when local == remote (identical hash)\\n\\n- **`doPushBranch(ctx, target, branchName)`**: Handles push with fetch+merge recovery\\n  - Tries push first with `git push --no-verify`\\n  - On non-fast-forward failure: fetches remote, calls `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch()`, then retries push\\n  - Prints progress messages to stderr with \\\"...\\\" dots\\n  - Returns nil (never fails - logs warnings instead)\\n\\n- **`fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon(ctx, target, branchName)`**: Fetches and merges sessions from remote\\n  - Uses temp ref (`refs/entire-fetch-tmp/<branch>`) when target is URL (avoids polluting remote-tracking namespace)\\n  - Uses standard remote-tracking ref when target is remote name\\n  - **Critical**: Calls `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch()` BEFORE merging trees (prevents silent unrelated history combining)\\n  - Flattens both local + remote trees and merges entries (session logs have unique `cond-*` directories, no conflicts)\\n  - Creates merge commit with two parents\\n  - Cleans up temp ref on exit (best-effort)\\n\\n**Error Handling:**\\n- Non-fast-forward detected: `strings.Contains(output, \\\"non-fast-forward\\\")` or `\\\"rejected\\\"`\\n- Fetch timeout: 2 minutes\\n- All errors logged but don't propagate (hooks must be silent)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. **Checkpoint Remote Configuration** (`checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Key Functions & Signatures:**\\n\\n- **`resolvePushSettings(ctx, pushRemoteName)`**: Loads settings once and resolves push config\\n  - Returns `pushSettings` struct with: `remote`, `checkpointURL`, `pushDisabled`\\n  - **One-time fetch**: Calls `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing()` only if branch doesn't exist locally\\n  - After first resolution, subsequent calls are no-op network-wise (branch exists locally)\\n  - Fork detection: Compares `config.Owner()` with parsed push remote owner (case-insensitive)\\n  - If fork detected: Falls back to using `remote` name instead of checkpoint URL\\n\\n- **`parseGitRemoteURL(rawURL)`**: Parses git URLs into components\\n  - Supports: SSH SCP (`git@host:org/repo`), HTTPS (`https://host/org/repo`), SSH protocol (`ssh://git@host/org/repo`)\\n  - Returns `gitRemoteInfo` struct: `{protocol, host, owner, repo}`\\n  - Protocol detection: \\\"ssh\\\" or \\\"https\\\"\\n\\n- **`deriveCheckpointURL(pushRemoteURL, config)`**: Constructs checkpoint URL matching push remote protocol\\n  - If push remote is SSH: generates `git@host:org/repo.git`\\n  - If push remote is HTTPS: generates `https://host/org/repo.git`\\n  - Uses `config.Repo` field (e.g., \\\"org/checkpoints\\\")\\n\\n- **`fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing(ctx, remoteURL)`**: Fetches metadata branch only if missing locally\\n  - **One-time check per settings load**: Returns early if branch exists locally\\n  - Timeout: 30 seconds\\n  - Sets `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` to prevent interactive auth prompts\\n  - Silently swallows fetch failures (returns nil): remote may be unreachable or branch doesn't exist yet\\n  - **Critical design**: Only returns fatal errors (opening repo, creating local branch), not network issues\\n  - On success: Creates local branch from fetched ref, cleans up temp ref (best-effort)\\n\\n**Settings Structure:**\\n```go\\ntype CheckpointRemoteConfig struct {\\n    Provider string // \\\"github\\\"\\n    Repo     string // \\\"org/checkpoints-repo\\\"\\n}\\n\\n// Accessed via: settings.GetCheckpointRemote()\\n// Returns nil if: not configured, wrong type, missing provider/repo, no slash in repo\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. **PrePush Hook Implementation** (`manual_commit_push.go`)\\n\\n**Signature & Flow:**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrePush(ctx, remote string) error\\n```\\n\\n1. Resolves push settings once: `ps := resolvePushSettings(ctx, remote)`\\n2. **Checkpoints branch** (entire/checkpoints/v1):\\n   - If NOT disabled (`!ps.pushDisabled`):\\n     - Push to `ps.pushTarget()` (checkpoint URL if configured, else remote name)\\n     - Uses `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.pushTarget(), paths.MetadataBranchName)`\\n3. **Trails branch** (entire/trails/v1):\\n   - ALWAYS push to user's push remote, never checkpoint remote\\n   - Uses `pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.remote, paths.TrailsBranchName)`\\n   - Note: `ps.remote` is unchanged (not affected by checkpoint URL)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. **Metadata Reconciliation** (`metadata_reconcile.go`)\\n\\n**Key Concept: The Empty-Orphan Bug**\\n\\nTwo metadata branches are \\\"disconnected\\\" when they share NO common ancestor (not just diverged). This only happens due to the empty-orphan bug where an empty commit was created on the orphan branch.\\n\\n**Key Functions:**\\n\\n- **`ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(ctx, repo, w)`**: Detects and repairs disconnected branches\\n  - Checks for disconnection using `git merge-base` (exit code 1 = no common ancestor)\\n  - Collects local commits oldest-first via `collectCommitChain()`\\n  - **Filters out empty commits** (the orphan bug artifact)\\n  - Cherry-picks non-empty commits onto remote tip via `cherryPickOnto()`\\n  - Each cherry-pick: computes full delta (additions, modifications, deletions) and applies to current tip\\n  - Updates local branch ref to new tip after all picks\\n  - Writes progress to stderr\\n\\n- **`IsMetadataDisconnected(ctx, repo)`**: Checks if disconnection exists\\n  - Returns false if either branch missing or they point to same hash\\n  - Uses `isDisconnected()` which wraps `git merge-base`\\n\\n**Exit Codes:**\\n- `git merge-base`: 0 = shared ancestry, 1 = no common ancestor, 128+ = error\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **Session Condensation** (`manual_commit_condensation.go`)\\n\\n**Key Concept**: Condenses shadow branch session data to permanent metadata branch\\n\\n**`CondenseSession()` Signature:**\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) CondenseSession(\\n    ctx context.Context,\\n    repo *git.Repository,\\n    checkpointID id.CheckpointID,\\n    state *SessionState,\\n    committedFiles map[string]struct{},\\n    opts ...condenseOpts,\\n) (*CondenseResult, error)\\n```\\n\\n**Flow:**\\n1. Gets shadow branch (or uses pre-resolved ref if available)\\n2. Extracts session data:\\n   - If shadow branch exists: `extractSessionData()` from shadow branch tree\\n   - Else (mid-session commit): `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` from live transcript file\\n3. Filters files_touched to only include committed files (1:1 checkpoint model)\\n4. Calculates attribution using HEAD tree vs shadow tree\\n5. Generates summary if enabled (calls `summarize.GenerateFromTranscript()`)\\n6. Writes to metadata branch via `store.WriteCommitted()`\\n\\n**Data Sources (Transcript):**\\n- Prefers live transcript file if readable (handles case where SaveStep was skipped but transcript continued)\\n- Falls back to shadow branch copy\\n- For OpenCode: Calls `prepareTranscriptIfNeeded()` to ensure export is flushed\\n\\n**Attribution Base Commit:**\\n- Tracks `state.AttributionBaseCommit` (normally = `state.BaseCommit`)\\n- Used for non-agent file detection when calculating attribution\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. **Session Logging** (`manual_commit_logs.go`)\\n\\n**Key Functions:**\\n\\n- **`listCheckpoints()`**: Lists all checkpoints from metadata branch\\n  - Uses `store.ListCommitted()` which reads from `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n  - Returns `[]CheckpointInfo` with: ID, SessionID, CreatedAt, FilesTouched, Agent, etc.\\n\\n- **`getCheckpointLog(checkpointID)`**: Retrieves transcript for specific checkpoint\\n  - Uses `store.ReadLatestSessionContent(checkpointID)`\\n  - Returns transcript bytes\\n\\n- **`GetAdditionalSessions()`**: Returns active sessions from `.git/entire-sessions/`\\n  - Lists sessions that haven't yet been condensed\\n  - For each: tries to get description from shadow branch\\n  - Session 