/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"86e3df20-d161-4e13-9659-f5963caf50f0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T15:43:11.940Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Weu3rQy1QENgVAftBcbo1v\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01YQMw4PcEy6YS7QQWWGvkCZ\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Remote Operations Tests - Summary\\n\\n## What was implemented\\n\\n### Infrastructure helpers (testenv.go)\\n- `SetupBareRemote()` - creates a bare git repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD\\n- `SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` - same with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n- `CloneFrom(bareDir)` - clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new TestEnv with `.entire/` initialized; respects the current branch (fixes bare repo HEAD mismatch)\\n- `BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` - checks branch existence on bare remote via `git show-ref`\\n- `PatchSettings(extra)` - merges keys into `.entire/settings.json`\\n- `GitPush(remote, refSpec)` - pushes a branch to remote\\n- `GitFetch(remote, args...)` - fetches from remote\\n\\n### P0 Tests - PrePush Basic Flow (4 tests)\\n1. **TestPrePush_PushesCheckpointBranchToOrigin** - session + condense + PrePush verifies `entire/checkpoints/v1` arrives on bare remote with checkpoint metadata\\n2. **TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenItExists** - verifies trails branch is pushed when present locally\\n3. **TestPrePush_NoOpWhenNoCheckpoints** - no session activity => PrePush succeeds silently, no branches on remote\\n4. **TestPrePush_IdempotentWhenAlreadyPushed** - push twice, remote ref unchanged on second push\\n\\n### P0 Tests - Checkpoint Remote Config (1 test)\\n5. **TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints** - `push_sessions: false` => checkpoint branch NOT on remote\\n\\n### P0 Tests - Clone and Resume (4 tests)\\n6. **TestCloneAndResume_FetchesCheckpointMetadata** - push checkpoints, clone, fetch metadata branch, verify checkpoint data present\\n7. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionListingWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch metadata, verify `ls-tree` finds checkpoint IDs\\n8. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionLogRetrievalWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, read transcript from metadata branch tree\\n9. **TestCloneAndResume_NewSessionPushAppends** - push from repo A, clone as B, new session in B, push => remote has BOTH checkpoints\\n\\n### P1 Tests - Non-Fast-Forward Recovery (1 test)\\n10. **TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries** - two clones push concurrently; second gets non-fast-forward, fetch+merge+retry succeeds; both checkpoints on remote\\n\\n### P1 Tests - Graceful Degradation (1 test)\\n11. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableRemotePushContinues** - PrePush succeeds without error when pushing to origin\\n\\n## Tests added\\n- 11 integration tests in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/remote_operations_test.go`\\n- 7 infrastructure methods in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go`\\n\\n## Design decisions and trade-offs\\n\\n1. **CloneFrom respects current branch**: The bare repo's HEAD may point to a non-existent default branch when the original env was on a feature branch. `CloneFrom` explicitly passes `--branch <currentBranch>` to `git clone` to avoid detached HEAD issues.\\n\\n2. **Trails branch test is conditional**: The trails branch is only created by the trail subsystem during condensation under certain configurations. The test verifies push behavior when the branch exists but does not fail if it doesn't. This avoids coupling to trail creation internals.\\n\\n3. **Concurrent push test reads checkpoint ID before push**: After a fetch+merge, the latest commit on the metadata branch is a merge commit without a \\\"Checkpoint:\\\" subject. The test reads B's checkpoint ID before pushing, avoiding the need to walk the merge commit history.\\n\\n4. **No checkpoint_remote routing test with local paths**: The `resolvePushSettings` pipeline derives checkpoint URLs from SSH/HTTPS URLs, not local paths. Testing the full routing pipeline would require mock URLs. This is already well-covered at the unit level in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. The integration tests focus on the push/fetch mechanics that unit tests cannot exercise.\\n\\n5. **ListCheckpoints in clone uses git ls-tree**: Instead of calling the CLI binary's `entire sessions` command (which would require additional env setup), the test reads checkpoint IDs directly from the metadata branch tree using `git ls-tree`. This is simpler and tests the same underlying data.\\n\\n## Issues encountered\\n\\n1. **Bare repo HEAD mismatch**: `git init --bare` creates HEAD pointing to `refs/heads/main`, but when the original env pushes from `feature/test-branch`, cloning the bare repo would try to check out `main` (which doesn't exist). Fixed by passing `--branch` to `git clone`.\\n\\n2. **Session state not created in clones**: The clone's `git clone` creates a fresh `.git/` without `entire-sessions/`. This is expected behavior -- sessions are created fresh by the hooks in the clone.\\n\\n## Suggested next steps\\n\\n- **P0: Fork detection test** - Test that checkpoint_remote with different owner skips push (already covered at unit level, but could add integration-level test)\\n- **P1: Disconnected metadata (empty-orphan recovery)** test at integration level\\n- **P2: Push after rebase** - shadow branch migration + push\\n- **P2: Fetch timeout** - verify bounded timeout for `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cach