"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_0121sYXNXSRsyooRXoPGh3C9\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Remote Operations Tests -- Summary\\n\\n## What Was Implemented\\n\\nAddressed all critical and important feedback items from review-01, plus added missing P0 and P1 test coverage.\\n\\n### Critical Fixes\\n\\n1. **Refactored `runPrePushInDir` to `env.RunPrePush(remote)` method** (testenv.go)\\n   - Added `RunPrePush` and `RunPrePushWithError` methods on `TestEnv`\\n   - Uses `env.cliEnv()` consistently with all other CLI invocations (RunCLI, GitCommitWithShadowHooks, etc.)\\n   - Includes `ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR`, `ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR`, `ENTIRE_TEST_OPENCODE_PROJECT_DIR`, and `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0`\\n   - Removed the standalone `runPrePushInDir` function entirely\\n\\n2. **Fixed graceful degradation test** (`TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues`)\\n   - Now actually tests unreachable checkpoint remote scenario\\n   - Pushes checkpoints to a non-existent path (simulating unreachable checkpoint URL)\\n   - Verifies PrePush does not error, trails still arrive on origin\\n\\n### Important Fixes\\n\\n3. **Trails push test now properly asserts trails are pushed** (`TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent`)\\n   - Renamed from `TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenItExists` to clarify semantics\\n   - If trails branch doesn't exist locally (trails require explicit \\\"trail start\\\"), creates a minimal orphan branch to test the push mechanism\\n   - Uses go-git plumbing to create the orphan branch without switching the working tree\\n\\n4. **`push_sessions: false` test verifies trails ARE still pushed** (`TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints`)\\n   - Added assertion that `entire/trails/v1` is on remote even when `push_sessions` is false\\n   - Conditional on trails existing locally (since trails creation depends on trail start)\\n\\n5. **Clone tests documented why they bypass `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`**\\n   - Added `FetchMetadataBranch` method to TestEnv (with `t.Fatalf` on error, not silently swallowing)\\n   - Added clear documentation in each clone test explaining: `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` uses `OpenRepository` which requires CWD inside the repo (incompatible with `t.Parallel()`), and the production function is tested directly in `checkpoint_remote_test.go` (`TestFetchBranchIfMissing_*`)\\n\\n6. **Concurrent push test verifies merge commit has 2 parents** (`TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries`)\\n   - Added `GetBranchTipParentCount` method on TestEnv\\n   - Asserts clone B's metadata branch tip has 2 parents after the fetch+merge+retry\\n\\n### New P0 Tests (Coverage Gap 7)\\n\\n7. **`TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote`**\\n   - Creates two bare remotes (origin + checkpoint-store)\\n   - Pushes checkpoints directly to the checkpoint bare repo path (simulating `pushBranchIfNeeded` with a resolved checkpoint URL)\\n   - Verifies checkpoints are on checkpoint remote, NOT on origin\\n   - Verifies trails are on origin, NOT on checkpoint remote\\n   - Documented why: `resolvePushSettings` derives URLs from origin's protocol (SSH/HTTPS), but local path remotes can't be parsed as URLs, so we test at the `pushBranchIfNeeded` level\\n\\n8. **`TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin`**\\n   - Configures `checkpoint_remote` with a different owner than the push remote\\n   - Runs PrePush; since origin is a local path (unparseable as URL), checkpoint URL derivation fails\\n   - Verifies checkpoints fall back to origin\\n   - Cross-references the unit test `TestResolvePushSettings_ForkDetection` which validates the exact fork detection logic with real URL parsing\\n\\n### New P1 Tests (Coverage Gap 8)\\n\\n9. **`TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent`**\\n   - Clones a repo, configures checkpoint_remote to nonexistent org/repo\\n   - Verifies session starts cleanly\\n   - Verifies PrePush doesn't fail (falls back to origin)\\n\\n### Helper Improvements\\n\\n- **`createCheckpointedCommit`** helper reduces boilerplate: encapsulates the entire session setup (NewSession -> CreateTranscript -> SimulateUserPromptSubmit -> WriteFile -> GitAdd -> SimulateStop -> GitCommitWithShadowHooks) into one call\\n- **`createOrphanBranch`** uses go-git plumbing to create orphan branches without switching the working tree\\n- **`pushBranchToTarget` / `pushBranchToTargetWithError`** helpers for direct `git push` to arbitrary targets\\n\\n## Infrastructure Additions to testenv.go\\n\\n- `env.RunPrePush(remote)` -- runs pre-push hook via CLI binary with `env.cliEnv()`\\n- `env.RunPrePushWithError(remote)` -- same but returns error\\n- `env.FetchMetadataBranch(remoteURL)` -- fetches metadata branch with `t.Fatalf` on error\\n- `env.GetBranchTipParentCount(branchName)` -- returns parent count for branch tip commit\\n\\n## Decisions and Trade-offs\\n\\n1. **Trails branch**: Trails are only created when a trail is explicitly started. The basic session + commit flow does not create trails. Tests that need to verify trail push behavior create a minimal orphan branch using go-git plumbing.\\n\\n2. **Checkpoint remote routing with local paths**: The production `resolvePushSettings` derives checkpoint URLs from origin's SSH/HTTPS protocol. Since test remotes use local file paths (not URLs), `parseGitRemoteURL` cannot parse them. The routing test therefore operates at the `pushBranchIfNeeded` / `git push` level, which is what PrePush ultimately calls. The URL derivation logic is covered by unit tests in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`.\\n\\n3. **Clone tests vs `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`**: The production function uses `OpenRepository` which resolves from CWD. Integration tests use `t.Parallel()` which is incompatible with `t.Chdir()`. The clone tests use raw `git fetch` (via `env.FetchMetadataBranch`) and document this clearly. The production code path is covered by dedicated unit tests (`TestFetchBranchIfMissing_*`) which use `t.Chdir()` and are not parallel.\\n\\n## Not Implemented (Deferred)\\n\\n- **Disconnected metadata recovery during concurrent push** (P1): Would need to set up the empty-orphan bug artifact, which requires internal knowledge of how the bug manifests. Deferred to a separate task.\\n- **Fetch timeout test** (P2): Requires a slow/hanging remote, which is difficult to simulate in integration tests.\\n- **PrePush with URL target** (P2): Tested implicitly by `TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote` which pushes to a bare repo path.\\n- **Fetch is one-time no-op** (P2): Covered by unit test `TestFetchBranchIfMissing_NoOpWhenBranchExistsLocally`.\\n- **Push after rebase** (P2): Requires complex shadow branch migration setup.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- `mise run fmt` -- clean\\n- `mise run lint` -- 0 issues\\n- `mise run test:ci` -- all tests pass (unit + integration + 43/43 E2E canary)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":220,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":112410,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":220,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3FnhgvQWCubTvVY7ah4\",\"uuid\":\"3f2b157a-d3a6-42a7-855e-0994d934a88f\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"18aa5c6f-5bcb-473c-ab18-6aad940a47d3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:35.428Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tes