\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3FrKzog9EPDe9ot4Mu6\",\"uuid\":\"dbcc77dd-26e5-4850-8bbd-2b5692d8f318\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"cc5b0319-dfda-4445-abf8-802128ec12a0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:39.510Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cc5b0319-dfda-4445-abf8-802128ec12a0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CDJ6BDJjjQDkfLzUKEjbQL\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"31377db1-af84-4b4b-b6b6-a2c24cd36914\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:39.634Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"2650fe06-f5c2-4b97-b5e4-b9038965cb8b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:39.635Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2650fe06-f5c2-4b97-b5e4-b9038965cb8b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:42.597Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01JjLmN1Ak99wiecMzNUxw98\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_019W5WCiKVY1mXSmHTmXXM18\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":145,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":114714,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":145,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":25,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3Frdz3FkUrgQVAw8Vjd\",\"uuid\":\"340b5810-12ab-42e3-a025-96a5f12ce3ea\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"ac18a194-d4c7-48ad-a5a2-00f55bb08e94\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:42.598Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ac18a194-d4c7-48ad-a5a2-00f55bb08e94\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019W5WCiKVY1mXSmHTmXXM18\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Remote Operations Tests - Summary\\n     2→\\n     3→## What was implemented\\n     4→\\n     5→### Infrastructure helpers (testenv.go)\\n     6→- `SetupBareRemote()` - creates a bare git repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD\\n     7→- `SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` - same with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n     8→- `CloneFrom(bareDir)` - clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new TestEnv with `.entire/` initialized; respects the current branch (fixes bare repo HEAD mismatch)\\n     9→- `BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` - checks branch existence on bare remote via `git show-ref`\\n    10→- `PatchSettings(extra)` - merges keys into `.entire/settings.json`\\n    11→- `GitPush(remote, refSpec)` - pushes a branch to remote\\n    12→- `GitFetch(remote, args...)` - fetches from remote\\n    13→\\n    14→### P0 Tests - PrePush Basic Flow (4 tests)\\n    15→1. **TestPrePush_PushesCheckpointBranchToOrigin** - session + condense + PrePush verifies `entire/checkpoints/v1` arrives on bare remote with checkpoint metadata\\n    16→2. **TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenItExists** - verifies trails branch is pushed when present locally\\n    17→3. **TestPrePush_NoOpWhenNoCheckpoints** - no session activity => PrePush succeeds silently, no branches on remote\\n    18→4. **TestPrePush_IdempotentWhenAlreadyPushed** - push twice, remote ref unchanged on second push\\n    19→\\n    20→### P0 Tests - Checkpoint Remote Config (1 test)\\n    21→5. **TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints** - `push_sessions: false` => checkpoint branch NOT on remote\\n    22→\\n    23→### P0 Tests - Clone and Resume (4 tests)\\n    24→6. **TestCloneAndResume_FetchesCheckpointMetadata** - push checkpoints, clone, fetch metadata branch, verify checkpoint data present\\n    25→7. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionListingWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch metadata, verify `ls-tree` finds checkpoint IDs\\n    26→8. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionLogRetrievalWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, read transcript from metadata branch tree\\n    27→9. **TestCloneAndResume_NewSessionPushAppends** - push from repo A, clone as B, new session in B, push => remote has BOTH checkpoints\\n    28→\\n    29→### P1 Tests - Non-Fast-Forward Recovery (1 test)\\n    30→10. **TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries** - two clones push concurrently; second gets non-fast-forward, fetch+merge+retry succeeds; both checkpoints on remote\\n    31→\\n    32→### P1 Tests - Graceful Degradation (1 test)\\n    33→11. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableRemotePushContinues** - PrePush succeeds without error when pushing to origin\\n    34→\\n    35→## Tests added\\n    36→- 11 integration tests in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/remote_operations_test.go`\\n    37→- 7 infrastructure methods in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go`\\n    38→\\n    39→## Design decisions and trade-offs\\n    40→\\n    41→1. **CloneFrom respects current branch**: The bare repo's HEAD may point to a non-existent default branch when the original env was on a feature branch. `CloneFrom` explicitly passes `--branch <currentBranch>` to `git clone` to avoid detached HEAD issues.\\n    42→\\n    43→2. **Trails branch test is conditional**: The trails branch is only created by the trail subsystem during condensation under certain configurations. The test verifies push behavior when the branch exists but does not fail if it doesn't. This avoids coupling to trail creation internals.\\n    44→\\n    45→3. **Concurrent push test reads checkpoint ID before push**: After a fetch+merge, the latest commit on the metadata branch is a merge commit without a \\\"Checkpoint:\\\" subject. The test reads B's checkpoint ID before pushing, avoiding the need to walk the merge commit history.\\n    46→\\n    47→4. **No checkpoint_remote routing test with local paths**: The `resolvePushSettings` pipeline derives checkpoint URLs from SSH/HTTPS URLs, not local paths. Testing the full routing pipeline would require mock URLs. This is already well-covered at the unit level in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. The integration tests focus on the push/fetch mechanics that unit tests cannot exercise.\\n    48→\\n    49→5. **ListCheckpoints in clone uses git ls-tree**: Instead of calling the CLI binary's `entire sessions` command (which would require additional env setup), the test reads checkpoint IDs directly from the metadata branch tree using `git ls-tree`. This is simpler and tests the same underlying data.\\n    50→\\n    51→## Issues encountered\\n    52→\\n    53→1. **Bare repo HEAD mismatch**: `git init --bare` creates HEAD pointing to `refs/heads/main`, but when the original env pushes from `feature/test-branch`, cloning the bare repo would try to check out `main` (which doesn't exist). Fixed by passing `--branch` to `git clone`.\\n    54→\\n    55→2. **Session state not created in clones**: The clone's `git clone` creates a fresh `.git/` without `entire-sessions/`. This is expected behavior -- sessions are created fresh by the hooks in the clone.\\n    56→\\n    57→## Suggested next steps\\n    58→\\n    59→- **P0: Fork detection test** - Test that checkpoint_remote with different owner skips push (already covered at unit level, but could add integration-level test)\\n    60→- **P1: Disconnected metadata (empty-orphan recovery)** test at integration level\\n    61→- **P2: Push after rebase** - shadow branch migration + push\\n    62→- **P2: Fetch timeout** - verify bounded timeout for `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`\\n    63→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"1dc544dc-6bc5-474f-8c72-0630a70fe0b0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:42.603Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"a3f87257-8609-4bdc-bdc1-558d29d622b9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:04:42.607Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a3f87257-8609-4bdc-bdc1-558d29d622b9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:05:07.055Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PJkA9nrJuyRByZHQn5dLan\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_011BGUnWQ4UABZfNYH7DtvX3\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Remote Operations Tests -- Summary\\n\\n## What Was Implemented\\n\\n### Infrastructure helpers (testenv.go)\\n\\nOriginal infrastructure (from task-01):\\n- `SetupBareRemote()` - creates a bare git repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD\\n- `SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` - same with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n- `CloneFrom(bareDir)` - clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new TestEnv with `.entire/` initialized\\n- `BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` - checks branch existence on bare remote\\n- `PatchSettings(extra)` - merges keys into `.entire/settings.json`\\n- `GitPush(remote, refSpec)` - pushes a branch to remote\\n- `GitFetch(remote, args...)` - fetches from remote\\n\\nNew infrastructure (from review-01 fixes):\\n- `RunPrePush(remote)` - runs pre-push hook via CLI binary with `env.cliEnv()` (replaces standalone `runPrePushInDir`)\\n- `RunPrePushWithError(remote)` - same but returns error\\n- `FetchMetadataBranch(remoteURL)` - fetches metadata branch with `t.Fatalf` on error\\n- `GetBranchTipParentCount(branchName)` - returns parent count for branch tip commit\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- PrePush Basic Flow (4 tests)\\n1. **TestPrePush_PushesCheckpointBranchToOrigin** - session + condense + PrePush verifies `entire/checkpoints/v1` arrives on bare remote with checkpoint metadata\\n2. **TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent** - creates trails branch if not present, verifies push mechanism works\\n3. **TestPrePush_NoOpWhenNoCheckpoints** - no session activity => PrePush succeeds silently, no branches on remote\\n4. **TestPrePush_IdempotentWhenAlreadyPushed** - push twice, remote ref unchanged on second push\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- Checkpoint Remote Config (3 tests)\\n5. **TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints** - `push_sessions: false` => checkpoints NOT on remote, trails still pushed\\n6. **TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote** - two bare remotes, checkpoints to checkpoint remote, trails to origin\\n7. **TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin** - different owner in checkpoint_remote, checkpoints fall back to origin\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- Clone and Resume (4 tests)\\n8. **TestCloneAndResume_FetchesCheckpointMetadata** - push, clone, fetch metadata branch, verify data present\\n9. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionListingWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, verify checkpoint IDs discoverable\\n10. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionLogRetrievalWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, read transcript content\\n11. **TestCloneAndResume_NewSessionPushAppends** - push from A, clone as B, new session + push => remote has both\\n\\n### P1 Tests -- Non-Fast-Forward Recovery (1 test)\\n12. **TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries** - two clones push concurrently; verifies merge commit with 2 parents\\n\\n### P1 Tests -- Graceful Degradation (2 tests)\\n13. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues** - unreachable checkpoint remote does not fail push, trails still arrive on origin\\n14. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent** - clone + unreachable checkpoint_remote, session starts cleanly\\n\\n### Helper Functions\\n- `createCheckpointedCommit` - reduces 8+ lines of boilerplate per session setup to one call\\n- `createOrphanBranch` - creates orphan branches via go-git plumbing (no working tree switch)\\n- `pushBranchToTarget` / `pushBranchToTargetWithError` - direct `git push` to arbitrary targets\\n\\n## Review-01 Issues Addressed\\n\\n### Critical (2/2 fixed)\\n1. **`runPrePushInDir` uses wrong env pattern** -- Replaced with `env.RunPrePush(remote)` method using `env.cliEnv()`\\n2. **Graceful degradation test doesn't test degradation** -- Now configures unreachable checkpoint remote and verifies trails still push to origin\\n\\n### Important (4/4 fixed)\\n3. **Trails push test doesn't verify trails were actually pushed** -- Creates trails branch if missing, then asserts it arrives on remote\\n4. **`push_sessions: false` test doesn't verify trails ARE still pushed** -- Added assertion for trails on remote\\n5. **Clone-and-resume tests bypass production `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`** -- Added clear documentation explaining why (CWD-based `OpenRepository` incompatible with `t.Parallel`), cross-referenced production function unit tests, replaced silent error swallowing with `t.Fatalf`\\n6. **Concurrent push test doesn't verify merge commit has two parents** -- Added `GetBranchTipParentCount` method and assertion\\n\\n### Coverage Gaps (5/8 addressed)\\n7a. **checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote** -- Implemented at pushBranchIfNeeded level\\n7b. **fork detection falls back to origin** -- Implemented with checkpoint_remote config + local path fallback\\n8a. **Unreachable checkpoint remote on clone (fetch is silent)** -- Implemented\\n8b. **Disconnected metadata recovery during concurrent push** -- Deferred (requires empty-orphan bug artifact setup)\\n8c. **Fetch timeout test** -- Deferred (P2, requires slow remote simulation)\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **Trails branch creation**: Trails are only created via \\\"trail start\\\", not by basic session+commit. Tests that need trails create a minimal orphan branch using go-git plumbing APIs (avoids working tree conflicts).\\n\\n2. **Checkpoint remote routing with local paths**: `resolvePushSettings` derives URLs from origin's SSH/HTTPS protocol. Local path remotes can't be parsed as URLs. The routing test operates at the `pushBranchIfNeeded`/`git push` level. URL derivation is covered by unit tests in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`.\\n\\n3. **Clone tests vs `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`**: The production function uses `OpenRepository` (CWD-based), incompatible with `t.Parallel()`. Clone tests use raw `git fetch` via `env.FetchMetadataBranch` and document this clearly. Production code path covered by dedicated unit tests.\\n\\n4. **`createCheckpointedCommit` helper**: Reduces the repeated 8-line session setup pattern to a single call, making test intent clearer.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- `mise run fmt` -- clean\\n- `mise run lint` -- 0 issues\\n- `mise run test:ci` -- all tests pass (unit + integration + 43/43 E2E canary)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1655,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":114859,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":1655,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":24,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3FrrkzFQAjRhnYiDgAU\",\"uuid\":\"baf865c6-c66a-4334-99b9-908f5069c6a7\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aa12ae655c0e49cd3\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01W25dTGkeHhuYbrAbEFREk7\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01H5pnBGNiDQMxAbFMJYaBxj\",\"uuid\":\"47cf3856-8aa6-4d72-ac91-54edb2acd9de\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:05:07.056Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"47cf3856-8aa6-4d72-ac91-54edb2acd9de\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_011BGUnWQ4UABZfNYH7DtvX3\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"The file /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md has been updated successfully.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"2dd6c217-7e85-4204-8a86-4eb1b84d8187\",\"timestamp\":