toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01DTWBKLFYY4Tt2yMVT5byZS\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01P8ixmrGh4ePZngsVSQuhYh\",\"uuid\":\"47f8035c-28cb-465e-89a5-de39dcb64988\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:12:27.383Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"47f8035c-28cb-465e-89a5-de39dcb64988\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:09.344Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01MsCzy2EB5pqkwXZjy3Mvc3\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Xz65Z3ZzpQgRET9Sx65vb2\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/review-02.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 02\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-03-14\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n\\n## Files Reviewed\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go` (diff: +248 lines of infrastructure helpers)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/remote_operations_test.go` (new file, 914 lines)\\n\\n## Previous Review Status (review-01)\\n\\n### Critical Issues\\n\\n- [x] **`runPrePushInDir` uses `testutil.GitIsolatedEnv()` instead of `env.cliEnv()`** - FIXED. The standalone `runPrePushInDir` function has been replaced with `env.RunPrePush(remote)` and `env.RunPrePushWithError(remote)` methods on `TestEnv` that use `env.cliEnv()`. This is consistent with the rest of the test infrastructure (`GitCommitWithShadowHooks`, `RunCLI`, etc.).\\n\\n- [x] **`TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableRemotePushContinues` does not test what the requirements specify** - PARTIALLY FIXED. The test has been renamed to `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues` and restructured. It now attempts a push to a non-existent path (`nonExistentPath`) to simulate an unreachable checkpoint remote. However, the test still does not exercise the actual `PrePush` code path with a configured `checkpoint_remote` -- see New Findings below.\\n\\n### Important Issues\\n\\n- [x] **`TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenItExists` does not actually assert trails were pushed** - FIXED. The test has been renamed to `TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent` and restructured to guarantee the trails branch exists locally before pushing. It now creates an orphan `entire/trails/v1` branch via `createOrphanBranch()` if the standard flow does not create one, then asserts it arrives on the remote. The assertion is no longer conditional.\\n\\n- [x] **`TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints` does not verify trails behavior** - FIXED. The test now includes a trails assertion (lines 230-236). It checks whether the trails branch was created locally and, if so, asserts it arrived on remote. However, the assertion is still conditional on the branch existing (see Suggestions).\\n\\n- [ ] **Clone-and-resume tests manually fetch via `fetchMetadataBranch` instead of testing `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`** - PARTIALLY ADDRESSED. The test comments now explicitly document that `FetchMetadataBranch` tests the \\\"data arrives and is usable\\\" property, and that `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` is tested in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. The approach is intentional and documented. However, the requirements say \\\"start new session in B (triggers `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`)\\\" -- the integration tests still don't exercise this path end-to-end. The comment at line 412-417 explains this is due to `OpenRepository` requiring CWD (incompatible with `t.Parallel`). This is a reasonable design tradeoff, but worth noting that the integration tests do not validate the full `resolvePushSettings -> fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` flow.\\n\\n- [x] **`TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries` does not verify merge commit structure** - FIXED. The test now calls `cloneB.GetBranchTipParentCount(paths.MetadataBranchName)` and asserts 2 parents (line 613-616). The new `GetBranchTipParentCount` helper in `testenv.go` correctly uses go-git to inspect the commit's parent hashes.\\n\\n### Suggestions from review-01\\n\\n- [ ] **`PatchSettings` does shallow merge, not deep merge** - NOT ADDRESSED (acceptable, documented as low-priority).\\n\\n- [x] **`fetchMetadataBranch` helper swallows errors silently** - FIXED. Replaced with `FetchMetadataBranch` method on `TestEnv` that calls `t.Fatalf` on error (line 1834-1843).\\n\\n- [x] **`listCheckpointsInDir` reimplements checkpoint listing logic** - ADDRESSED. The function now has an explicit comment (line 879) explaining the intentional separate implementation: \\\"This intentionally uses a separate implementation (git ls-tree) rather than the production ListCheckpoints() to avoid testing the code with itself.\\\"\\n\\n- [ ] **`SetupBareRemote` / `SetupNamedBareRemote` -- consider checking for existing remote** - NOT ADDRESSED (low-priority, acceptable).\\n\\n- [x] **Reduce test boilerplate** - FIXED. The `createCheckpointedCommit` helper (line 384-406) encapsulates the full session lifecycle, significantly reducing duplication. It is used in 9 of the 13 test functions.\\n\\n### Coverage Gaps from review-01\\n\\n- [x] **\\\"checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote\\\"** - ADDED. `TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote` (line 247) tests routing with two bare remotes. However, it bypasses `resolvePushSettings` and calls `pushBranchToTarget` directly. See New Findings below.\\n\\n- [x] **\\\"fork detection skips checkpoint_remote, falls back to origin\\\"** - ADDED. `TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin` (line 323) configures `checkpoint_remote` with a different owner and runs PrePush. The test relies on the fact that local path remotes cannot be parsed by `parseGitRemoteURL`, causing fallback to origin.\\n\\n- [x] **\\\"unreachable checkpoint remote -- fetch on clone is silent\\\"** - ADDED. `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent` (line 696) tests that configuring a nonexistent checkpoint_remote in a clone does not break session start or PrePush.\\n\\n- [ ] **\\\"concurrent push with disconnected metadata (empty-orphan recovery)\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. The concurrent push test does exercise the reconciliation path (as visible in the test output: \\\"Detected disconnected session metadata... Cherry-picking 1 local checkpoint(s) onto remote...\\\"), but this happens incidentally rather than by design. There is no explicit test for the empty-orphan artifact scenario described in the requirements.\\n\\n- [ ] **\\\"clone with checkpoint_remote fetches from checkpoint URL\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. This P0 test is still missing.\\n\\n- [ ] **\\\"fetch timeout does not block push\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED (requirements noted this as P2/skip).\\n\\n- [ ] **P2 tests (URL target, one-time fetch, push after rebase)** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. These are P2 and not blocking.\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:282-287] `TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote` bypasses `PrePush` entirely.** The test calls `pushBranchToTarget(t, env.RepoDir, bareCheckpoint, paths.MetadataBranchName)` directly (a raw `git push` wrapper) instead of going through `env.RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` with settings that route checkpoints. This means the test verifies that `git push` to a path works (trivially true) and that branches can be selectively routed by the test code. It does NOT test the actual `PrePush -> resolvePushSettings -> pushTarget()` production code path. The comment at line 243-246 acknowledges this limitation (\\\"we test at the pushBranchIfNeeded level\\\") but `pushBranchIfNeeded` is not being called either -- it is a raw `git push`. The production logic in `resolvePushSettings` that determines _where_ to push (checkpoint URL vs origin) is not exercised at all. **Recommended fix:** Add a comment making this an explicit \\\"data routing verification\\\" test (not a production code path test), and consider whether a unit test for `resolvePushSettings` with mocked remotes would be more appropriate for the routing logic.\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:623-691] `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues` tests git push failure, not PrePush graceful degradation.** The test pushes directly to a non-existent path via `pushBranchToTargetWithError` (line 667), then runs a normal `env.RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` without any checkpoint_remote configuration. The production graceful degradation path is: `PrePush(\\\"origin\\\") -> resolvePushSettings resolves checkpointURL -> pushBranchIfNeeded(checkpointURL, ...) fails -> doPushBranch catches error and returns nil`. This test does not exercise that path at all. The push to the non-existent path is done by test code, not production code. Then the subsequent `RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` is just a normal push to origin (happy path). The assertion that checkpoints are on origin (line 688) is expected because there is no checkpoint_remote routing -- it is the default behavior. **This is the same fundamental issue as review-01 (Critical #2), repackaged but not actually fixed.** The test now shows a git push failure to a bad path, but the PrePush production code's graceful degradation (catching push failures in `doPushBranch` and returning nil) is still not exercised. **Recommended fix:** Since local file paths cannot be parsed by `resolvePushSettings` to produce a `checkpointURL`, the real graceful degradation path cannot be tested at the integration level without either (a) setting origin to an SSH-like URL and configuring checkpoint_remote to resolve to a bad path, or (b) testing `doPushBranch` directly with a non-existent URL-like target. Option (b) is more practical. Alternatively, clearly document that this scenario is covered by unit tests in `push_common_test.go` and remove the misleading integration test.\\n\\n- **[testenv.go / remote_operations_test.go] Lint violations will block CI.** Running `golangci-lint run --new-from-rev=main` produces 19 issues in the new code:\\n  - **`noctx` (14 in testenv.go, 4 in test file):** `exec.Command` without context. While existing code in testenv.go has the same pattern, these are *new* lines that CI's `golangci-lint-action@v9` will flag on a PR (it defaults to `only-new-issues: true`). The fix is to accept a `context.Context` parameter or use `exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), ...)`.\\n  - **`unparam` (2):** `sessionID` return value in `createCheckpointedCommit` is never used; `branchName` parameter in `fileExistsOnRemoteBranch` always receives `paths.MetadataBranchName`. Either use or remove the unused return/parameter.\\n  - **`wrapcheck` (1 in testenv.go:1826):** `RunPrePushWithError` returns an unwrapped error from `cmd.CombinedOutput()`. Since `testenv.go` is not a `_test.go` file, the `wrapcheck` exclusion for test files does not apply. Wrap the error with `fmt.Errorf`.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:230-236] Trails assertion in `TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints` is still conditional.** If the trails branch is never created locally, the test logs a message and passes without verifying trails behavior. This makes the test weaker than the requirements demand (\\\"entire/trails/v1 IS on remote\\\"). Consider using the same `createOrphanBranch` approach from `TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent` to guarantee the branch exists.\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:324-374] `TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin` relies on URL parse failure, not fork detection.** The test configures `checkpoint_remote` with `different-org/checkpoints`, but since origin is a local file path, `parseGitRemoteURL` fails before fork detection logic runs. The test comment (line 330-337) acknowledges this and references a unit test in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. This is an acceptable approach -- the test verifies the integration behavior (\\\"checkpoints still land on origin when checkpoint URL derivation fails\\\"). Consider renaming the test to `REDACTED` to more accurately describe what it actually tests.\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:384] `createCheckpointedCommit` could return only `checkpointID`.** Since `sessionID` is never used at any call site, removing it simplifies the API and fixes the `unparam` lint issue simultaneously.\\n\\n- **[testenv.go:1780] `PatchSettings` writes with 0o644 permissions.** The `gosec` linter flags this as G306 (expects 0600 or less for WriteFile). Settings files likely don't contain secrets in tests, but changing to 0o600 silences the warning at no cost.\\n\\n- **[remote_operations_test.go:696-743] `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent` could assert more.** The test verifies that session start and PrePush don't error, but doesn't verify that the session actually _works_ (e.g., checkpoint is created locally, data can be read). Adding a `cloneEnv.BranchExists(paths.MetadataBranchName)` assertion after the commit would strengthen the test.\\n\\n### Praise\\n\\n- Excellent fix for the `runPrePushInDir` issue -- `RunPrePush` and `RunPrePushWithError` on TestEnv are clean, consistent with the rest of the infrastructure, and provide both fatal-on-error and return-error variants.\\n- The `createCheckpointedCommit` helper significantly reduces boilerplate. Tests are now shorter and the important parts (setup, assertions) are more prominent.\\n- `GetBranchTipParentCount` is a well-designed helper that correctly validates the merge commit structure in the concurrent push test.\\n- Good documentation in test comments explaining design tradeoffs (e.g., why `FetchMetadataBranch` is used instead of `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`, why checkpoint_remote routing is tested at a lower level).\\n- The `createOrphanBranch` helper is implemented correctly using go-git plumbing APIs instead of switching the working tree (which would conflict with parallel tests).\\n- `FetchMetadataBranch` on TestEnv (replacing the standalone helper) properly fatals on error, making test failures easier to diagnose.\\n- All 13 tests pass, run in parallel, and complete in ~12 seconds total.\\n- Good coverage progression: from 7 tests in review-01 to 13 tests now.\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n**Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES**\\n\\nSignificant progress since review-01. The critical `runPrePushInDir` issue is fully fixed. The test boilerplate reduction, merge commit verification, and trails branch test restructuring are all well done. New tests were added for checkpoint_remote routing, fork detection fallback, and clone with unreachable checkpoint remote.\\n\\nHowever, two important issues remain:\\n\\n1. **The graceful degradation test (review-01 Critical #2) is still not testing the production graceful degradation code path.** The test has been restructured to show a git push failing to a non-existent path, but the push is done by test code, not by `doPushBranch`. The production code's error handling (catch push failure, warn, return nil) is not exercised. This was the same fundamental problem flagged in review-01.\\n\\n2. **Lint violations will block CI.** The 19 new lint issues (noctx, unparam, wrapcheck) need to be addressed before the PR can pass CI checks. These are straightforward fixes.\\n\\n3. **The checkpoint_remote routing test bypasses production code.** While it verifies the data routing concept, it uses raw `git push` rather than `pushBranchIfNeeded` or `PrePush`. This should at minimum be documented clearly as a \\\"data integrity\\\" test, not a \\\"routing logic\\\" test.\\n\\n**Estimated effort to address:**\\n- Lint fixes: ~30 minutes (mechanical changes: add `context.Background()`, remove unused return, wrap error, fix permissions)\\n- Graceful degradation test: ~1 hour (either restructure to test `doPushBranch` directly with a bad URL-like target, or document why integration-level testing is not feasible and rely on unit tests)\\n- Checkpoint remote routing documentation: ~15 minutes (clarify in comments what is and isn't being tested)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":876,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":75908,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":876,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3GT7kLBSpuGp25aASVg\",\"uuid\":\"efe2ca47-0e95-49fa-9dd6-0a053cf2687e\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a311f9ab69e676ce2\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01DTWBKLFYY4Tt2yMVT5byZS\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01P8ixmrGh4ePZngsVSQuhYh\",\"uuid\":\"b9f26f45-032b-4a48-8183-59573a8f06dc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:09.346Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b9f26f45-032b-4a48-8183-59573a8f06dc\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Xz65Z3ZzpQgRET9Sx65vb2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/review-02.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"8c2f3707-a2c9-4973-91d1-83aca589b1ab\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:09.351Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a311f9ab69e676ce2\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01DTWBKLF