ssage\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_0144VfnJbueHPaVstESCt592\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Remote Operations Test Coverage\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→Add integration tests for git remote operations: pushing checkpoint/trails branches, fetching metadata from checkpoint remotes, clone-and-resume workflows, and non-fast-forward recovery. All tests use local bare repos as remotes (no network). No E2E/agent tests needed — hook plumbing level is sufficient.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Goals\\n     8→\\n     9→- Verify the PrePush hook correctly pushes `entire/checkpoints/v1` and `entire/trails/v1` to the right remotes\\n    10→- Verify checkpoint_remote config routes checkpoints to a separate remote while trails stay on origin\\n    11→- Verify clone-and-resume: cloning a repo fetches checkpoint metadata and allows session continuation\\n    12→- Verify non-fast-forward recovery (fetch + merge + retry) when two clones race\\n    13→- Verify graceful degradation when checkpoint remote is unreachable\\n    14→- Verify session discovery (`entire sessions` / `entire log`) works after clone with fetched metadata\\n    15→\\n    16→## Test Location\\n    17→\\n    18→All tests go in `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/` using the existing `TestEnv` infrastructure, extended with bare remote helpers.\\n    19→\\n    20→## Infrastructure Additions\\n    21→\\n    22→### Must Have (P0)\\n    23→\\n    24→- [ ] **Add bare remote helpers to integration test `testenv.go`**\\n    25→  - `env.SetupBareRemote()` — creates bare repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD (mirrors E2E helper)\\n    26→  - `env.SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` — same but with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n    27→  - `env.CloneFrom(bareDir)` — clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new `TestEnv`\\n    28→  - `env.BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` — checks if branch exists on bare remote\\n    29→  - `env.PatchSettings(extra map[string]any)` — merges keys into `.entire/settings.json` (like E2E `PatchSettings`)\\n    30→\\n    31→## Functional Requirements\\n    32→\\n    33→### P0 — PrePush Basic Flow\\n    34→\\n    35→These test the core push path that every user hits.\\n    36→\\n    37→- [ ] **Test: PrePush pushes checkpoint branch to origin**\\n    38→  Setup: bare remote as origin → session → SaveStep → condense (simulate post-commit) → PrePush(\\\"origin\\\")\\n    39→  Assert: `entire/checkpoints/v1` exists on bare remote, commit tree contains checkpoint metadata\\n    40→\\n    41→- [ ] **Test: PrePush pushes trails branch to origin**\\n    42→  Same setup, also verify `entire/trails/v1` arrives on bare remote\\n    43→\\n    44→- [ ] **Test: PrePush is no-op when no checkpoints exist**\\n    45→  Setup: bare remote → no session activity → PrePush(\\\"origin\\\")\\n    46→  Assert: no `entire/checkpoints/v1` on remote, no error\\n    47→\\n    48→- [ ] **Test: PrePush is no-op when already pushed (idempotent)**\\n    49→  Setup: push once → push again with no new checkpoints\\n    50→  Assert: second push succeeds, remote ref unchanged\\n    51→\\n    52→### P0 — Checkpoint Remote Config\\n    53→\\n    54→These test the separate checkpoint remote routing, which is the key feature for the clone-and-resume flow.\\n    55→\\n    56→- [ ] **Test: checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote**\\n    57→  Setup: two bare remotes (origin + checkpoint-remote) → configure `strategy_options.checkpoint_remote: {provider: \\\"github\\\", repo: \\\"org/checkpoints\\\"}` → BUT since we use local paths, we need to set the checkpoint remote URL directly via the push remote URL derivation. Alternative: set origin's push URL to an SSH-like format and have the checkpoint remote derive from it. Simpler approach: test `resolvePushSettings` integration with real remotes — set origin URL, configure checkpoint_remote, call PrePush, verify checkpoints land on checkpoint remote URL (bare repo path) and trails land on origin.\\n    58→\\n    59→  **Concrete approach:** Create two bare repos. Configure origin normally. For checkpoint_remote, since `deriveCheckpointURL` derives from the push remote's protocol+host, and we're using local paths (not URLs), we need to either:\\n    60→  - (a) Call `pushBranchIfNeeded` directly with the bare repo path as target, OR\\n    61→  - (b) Mock the settings resolution to return the second bare repo path as `checkpointURL`\\n    62→\\n    63→  Recommended: Test at the `PrePush` level by patching settings so `checkpoint_remote` resolves to the second bare repo. This tests the full routing logic.\\n    64→\\n    65→  Assert: `entire/checkpoints/v1` on checkpoint bare remote (not on origin), `entire/trails/v1` on origin (not on checkpoint remote)\\n    66→\\n    67→- [ ] **Test: push_sessions: false disables checkpoint push, trails still pushed**\\n    68→  Setup: bare remote → configure `push_sessions: false` → session + condense → PrePush\\n    69→  Assert: no `entire/checkpoints/v1` on remote, `entire/trails/v1` IS on remote\\n    70→\\n    71→- [ ] **Test: fork detection skips checkpoint_remote, falls back to origin**\\n    72→  Setup: configure checkpoint_remote with different owner than push remote → PrePush\\n    73→  Assert: checkpoints pushed to origin, not to checkpoint remote URL\\n    74→\\n    75→### P0 — Clone and Resume\\n    76→\\n    77→This is the primary user story: clone a repo where sessions were previously pushed, and resume working.\\n    78→\\n    79→- [ ] **Test: clone fetches checkpoint metadata on first session start**\\n    80→  Setup: repo A with bare remote → session → condense → push (checkpoints on remote) → clone into repo B → start new session in B (triggers `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`)\\n    81→  Assert: `entire/checkpoints/v1` exists locally in clone, contains checkpoint data from repo A\\n    82→\\n    83→- [ ] **Test: session listing works after clone**\\n    84→  Setup: same as above (clone with fetched metadata)\\n    85→  Assert: `ListCheckpoints()` returns checkpoints from the original repo's sessions\\n    86→\\n    87→- [ ] **Test: session log retrieval works after clone**\\n    88→  Setup: same as above\\n    89→  Assert: `getCheckpointLog(cpID)` returns transcript content from original session\\n    90→\\n    91→- [ ] **Test: clone + new session + push appends to existing metadata**\\n    92→  Setup: clone from remote with existing checkpoints → new session in clone → condense → push\\n    93→  Assert: remote's `entire/checkpoints/v1` now has BOTH original and new checkpoint data\\n    94→\\n    95→- [ ] **Test: clone with checkpoint_remote fetches from checkpoint URL**\\n    96→  Setup: push checkpoints to separate checkpoint remote → clone from origin (no checkpoints) → configure checkpoint_remote in clone → start session (triggers fetch from checkpoint URL)\\n    97→  Assert: clone has checkpoint metadata fetched from checkpoint remote, not origin\\n    98→\\n    99→### P1 — Non-Fast-Forward Recovery\\n   100→\\n   101→These test the race condition where two clones push to the same remote.\\n   102→\\n   103→- [ ] **Test: concurrent push — second pusher fetches, merges, retries**\\n   104→  Setup: two clones (A and B) of same bare remote → both create sessions + condense → A pushes → B pushes (gets non-fast-forward) → B should fetch+merge+retry\\n   105→  Assert: remote has checkpoints from BOTH A and B, B's local branch has merge commit with two parents\\n   106→\\n   107→- [ ] **Test: concurrent push with disconnected metadata (empty-orphan recovery)**\\n   108→  Setup: two clones where one has the empty-orphan bug artifact → both push\\n   109→  Assert: reconciliation repairs the disconnected history, remote has clean linear-ish history\\n   110→\\n   111→### P1 — Graceful Degradation\\n   112→\\n   113→- [ ] **Test: unreachable checkpoint remote — push continues silently**\\n   114→  Setup: configure checkpoint_remote pointing to non-existent path → session + condense → PrePush\\n   115→  Assert: no error returned (hooks must not fail), trails still pushed to origin, warning logged\\n   116→\\n   117→- [ ] **Test: unreachable checkpoint remote — fetch on clone is silent**\\n   118→  Setup: clone from origin → configure checkpoint_remote to non-existent path → start session\\n   119→  Assert: session starts normally, no error, `entire/checkpoints/v1` not created locally (nothing to fetch)\\n   120→\\n   121→- [ ] **Test: fetch timeout does not block push**\\n   122→  Verify that `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` has a bounded timeout (30s) and doesn't hang indefinitely. May be hard to test without a slow remote — could be P2 or skip.\\n   123→\\n   124→### P2 — Edge Cases\\n   125→\\n   126→- [ ] **Test: PrePush with URL target (not remote name)**\\n   127→  Setup: call `pushBranchIfNeeded` with bare repo path as URL directly\\n   128→  Assert: push succeeds, no remote-tracking ref check (URL path skips optimization)\\n   129→\\n   130→- [ ] **Test: fetch is one-time — second call is no-op**\\n   131→  Setup: fetch metadata branch → call fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing again\\n   132→  Assert: second call returns immediately (branch exists locally), no git fetch executed\\n   133→\\n   134→- [ ] **Test: push after rebase (shadow branch migration + push)**\\n   135→  Setup: session → checkpoint on shadow branch → simulate rebase (HEAD changes) → shadow branch migrates → condense → push\\n   136→  Assert: checkpoint metadata correctly references new base commit, pushes cleanly\\n   137→\\n   138→## Out of Scope\\n   139→\\n   140→- E2E tests with real agents (Vogon or otherwise) — integration level is sufficient\\n   141→- Testing actual SSH/HTTPS authentication — we use local path remotes\\n   142→- Testing the `entire push` CLI command (if it exists) — we test the strategy method directly\\n   143→- Performance testing of push/fetch operations\\n   144→- Multi-worktree push scenarios (separate effort)\\n   145→\\n   146→## Dependencies\\n   147→\\n   148→- Existing integration test infrastructure (`testenv.go`, `TestEnv`)\\n   149→- Strategy implementation (`push_common.go`, `checkpoint_remote.go`, `manual_commit_push.go`)\\n   150→- Checkpoint store (`checkpoint/` package)\\n   151→- Session state management (`session/` package)\\n   152→\\n   153→## Open Questions\\n   154→\\n   155→- [ ] How to make `resolvePushSettings` use a local bare repo path as `checkpointURL` in tests? Options: (a) patch settings + set origin URL to trigger derivation, (b) test at `pushBranchIfNeeded` level with explicit paths, (c) add test-only override. Need to check if `deriveCheckpointURL` works with local paths or only real URLs.\\n   156→- [ ] Should we test the `entire/trails/v1` branch content (not just existence)? Trails are always pushed to origin — do we need to verify trail content, or just that the branch arrives?\\n   157→- [ ] The `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` one-time behavior — is it per-process or persisted? If per-process, the clone test naturally exercises it (fresh process). If persisted, we need to reset state between calls.\\n   158→\\n   159→## Acceptance Criteria\\n   160→\\n   161→- All P0 tests pass with `mise run test:integration`\\n   162→- Tests use isolated temp repos with bare remotes (no network, no real repo pollution)\\n   163→- Tests follow existing conventions: `t.Parallel()`, `testutil.InitRepo`, feature branch env\\n   164→- No flaky async waits — integration tests call strategy methods directly (synchronous)\\n   165→- CI (`mise run test:ci`) passes with the new tests\\n   166→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"489f9bf4-2c65-4798-9c3c-df6a96b4e28e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:45.482Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"91510ead-422c-4d49-9df0-c1ac12a1bd82\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:45.929Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"91510ead-422c-4d49-9df0-c1ac12a1bd82\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:46.033Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01AhT569zWiuiLqzddhpFRm5\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017P9CSLPMpEQsAEF5CLvQxY\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/review-02.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":12268,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":6857,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":12268,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":6,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3Gcrgk46csU1zSMT51e\",\"uuid\":\"2ffc5cb1-cb10-44f2-bcdd-24b9f6678c48\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"ff6cf644-a05c-4cc7-8c43-2ac83ad42fa0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:46.033Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ff6cf644-a05c-4cc7-8c43-2ac83ad42fa0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_017P9CSLPMpEQsAEF5CLvQxY\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Review 02\\n     2→\\n     3→> Status: pending-dev\\n     4→> Date: 2026-03-14\\n     5→> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n     6→> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n     7→\\n     8→## Files Reviewed\\n     9→\\n    10→- `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go` (diff: +248 lines of infrastructure helpers)\\n    11→- `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/remote_operations_test.go` (new file, 914 lines)\\n    12→\\n    13→## Previous Review Status (review-01)\\n    14→\\n    15→### Critical Issues\\n    16→\\n    17→- [x] **`runPrePushInDir` uses `testutil.GitIsolatedEnv()` instead of `env.cliEnv()`** - FIXED. The standalone `runPrePushInDir` function has been replaced with `env.RunPrePush(remote)` and `env.RunPrePushWithError(remote)` methods on `TestEnv` that use `env.cliEnv()`. This is consistent with the rest of the test infrastructure (`GitCommitWithShadowHooks`, `RunCLI`, etc.).\\n    18→\\n    19→- [x] **`TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableRemotePushContinues` does not test what the requirements specify** - PARTIALLY FIXED. The test has been renamed to `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues` and restructured. It now attempts a push to a non-existent path (`nonExistentPath`) to simulate an unreachable checkpoint remote. However, the test still does not exercise the actual `PrePush` code path with a configured `checkpoint_remote` -- see New Findings below.\\n    20→\\n    21→### Important Issues\\n    22→\\n    23→- [x] **`TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenItExists` does not actually assert trails were pushed** - FIXED. The test has been renamed to `TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent` and restructured to guarantee the trails branch exists locally before pushing. It now creates an orphan `entire/trails/v1` branch via `createOrphanBranch()` if the standard flow does not create one, then asserts it arrives on the remote. The assertion is no longer conditional.\\n    24→\\n    25→- [x] **`TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints` does not verify trails behavior** - FIXED. The test now includes a trails assertion (lines 230-236). It checks whether the trails branch was created locally and, if so, asserts it arrived on remote. However, the assertion is still conditional on the branch existing (see Suggestions).\\n    26→\\n    27→- [ ] **Clone-and-resume tests manually fetch via `fetchMetadataBranch` instead of testing `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`** - PARTIALLY ADDRESSED. The test comments now explicitly document that `FetchMetadataBranch` tests the \\\"data arrives and is usable\\\" property, and that `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` is tested in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. The approach is intentional and documented. However, the requirements say \\\"start new session in B (triggers `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`)\\\" -- the integration tests still don't exercise this path end-to-end. The comment at line 412-417 explains this is due to `OpenRepository` requiring CWD (incompatible with `t.Parallel`). This is a reasonable design tradeoff, but worth noting that the integration tests do not validate the full `resolvePushSettings -> fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing` flow.\\n    28→\\n    29→- [x] **`TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries` does not verify merge commit structure** - FIXED. The test now calls `cloneB.GetBranchTipParentCount(paths.MetadataBranchName)` and asserts 2 parents (line 613-616). The new `GetBranchTipParentCount` helper in `testenv.go` correctly uses go-git to inspect the commit's parent hashes.\\n    30→\\n    31→### Suggestions from review-01\\n    32→\\n    33→- [ ] **`PatchSettings` does shallow merge, not deep merge** - NOT ADDRESSED (acceptable, documented as low-priority).\\n    34→\\n    35→- [x] **`fetchMetadataBranch` helper swallows errors silently** - FIXED. Replaced with `FetchMetadataBranch` method on `TestEnv` that calls `t.Fatalf` on error (line 1834-1843).\\n    36→\\n    37→- [x] **`listCheckpointsInDir` reimplements checkpoint listing logic** - ADDRESSED. The function now has an explicit comment (line 879) explaining the intentional separate implementation: \\\"This intentionally uses a separate implementation (git ls-tree) rather than the production ListCheckpoints() to avoid testing the code with itself.\\\"\\n    38→\\n    39→- [ ] **`SetupBareRemote` / `SetupNamedBareRemote` -- consider checking for existing remote** - NOT ADDRESSED (low-priority, acceptable).\\n    40→\\n    41→- [x] **Reduce test boilerplate** - FIXED. The `createCheckpointedCommit` helper (line 384-406) encapsulates the full session lifecycle, significantly reducing duplication. It is used in 9 of the 13 test functions.\\n    42→\\n    43→### Coverage Gaps from review-01\\n    44→\\n    45→- [x] **\\\"checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote\\\"** - ADDED. `TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote` (line 247) tests routing with two bare remotes. However, it bypasses `resolvePushSettings` and calls `pushBranchToTarget` directly. See New Findings below.\\n    46→\\n    47→- [x] **\\\"fork detection skips checkpoint_remote, falls back to origin\\\"** - ADDED. `TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin` (line 323) configures `checkpoint_remote` with a different owner and runs PrePush. The test relies on the fact that local path remotes cannot be parsed by `parseGitRemoteURL`, causing fallback to origin.\\n    48→\\n    49→- [x] **\\\"unreachable checkpoint remote -- fetch on clone is silent\\\"** - ADDED. `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent` (line 696) tests that configuring a nonexistent checkpoint_remote in a clone does not break session start or PrePush.\\n    50→\\n    51→- [ ] **\\\"concurrent push with disconnected metadata (empty-orphan recovery)\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. The concurrent push test does exercise the reconciliation path (as visible in the test output: \\\"Detected disconnected session metadata... Cherry-picking 1 local checkpoint(s) onto remote...\\\"), but this happens incidentally rather than by design. There is no explicit test for the empty-orphan artifact scenario described in the requirements.\\n    52→\\n    53→- [ ] **\\\"clone with checkpoint_remote fetches from checkpoint URL\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. This P0 test is still missing.\\n    54→\\n    55→- [ ] **\\\"fetch timeout does not block push\\\"** - NOT IMPLEMENTED (requirements noted this as P2/skip).\\n    56→\\n    57→- [ ] **P2 tests (URL target, one-time fetch, push after rebase)** - NOT IMPLEMENTED. These are P2 and not blocking.\\n    58→\\n    59→## New Findings\\n    60→\\n    61→### Critical (Must Fix)\\n    62→\\n    63→None.\\n    64→\\n    65→### Important (Should Fix)\\n    66→\\n    67→- **[remote_operations_test.go:282-287] `TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote` bypasses `PrePush` entirely.** The test calls `pushBranchToTarget(t, env.RepoDir, bareCheckpoint, paths.MetadataBranchName)` directly (a raw `git push` wrapper) instead of going through `env.RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` with settings that route checkpoints. This means the test verifies that `git push` to a path works (trivially true) and that branches can be selectively routed by the test code. It does NOT test the actual `PrePush -> resolvePushSettings -> pushTarget()` production code path. The comment at line 243-246 acknowledges this limitation (\\\"we test at the pushBranchIfNeeded level\\\") but `pushBranchIfNeeded` is not being called either -- it is a raw `git push`. The production logic in `resolvePushSettings` that determines _where_ to push (checkpoint URL vs origin) is not exercised at all. **Recommended fix:** Add a comment making this an explicit \\\"data routing verification\\\" test (not a production code path test), and consider whether a unit test for `resolvePushSettings` with mocked remotes would be more appropriate for the routing logic.\\n    68→\\n    69→- **[remote_operations_test.go:623-691] `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues` tests git push failure, not PrePush graceful degradation.** The test pushes directly to a non-existent path via `pushBranchToTargetWithError` (line 667), then runs a normal `env.RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` without any checkpoint_remote configuration. The production graceful degradation path is: `PrePush(\\\"origin\\\") -> resolvePushSettings resolves checkpointURL -> pushBranchIfNeeded(checkpointURL, ...) fails -> doPushBranch catches error and returns nil`. This test does not exercise that path at all. The push to the non-existent path is done by test code, not production code. Then the subsequent `RunPrePush(\\\"origin\\\")` is just a normal push to origin (happy path). The assertion that checkpoints are on origin (line 688) is expected because there is no checkpoint_remote routing -- it is the default behavior. **This is the same fundamental issue as review-01 (Critical #2), repackaged but not actually fixed.** The test now shows a git push failure to a bad path, but the PrePush production code's graceful degradation (catching push failures in `doPushBranch` and returning nil) is still not exercised. **Recommended fix:** Since local file paths cannot be parsed by `resolvePushSettings` to produce a `checkpointURL`, the real graceful degradation path cannot be tested at the integration level without either (a) setting origin to an SSH-like URL and configuring checkpoint_remote to resolve to a bad path, or (b) testing `doPushBranch` directly with a non-existent URL-like target. Option (b) is more practical. Alternatively, clearly document that this scenario is covered by unit tests in `push_common_test.go` and remove the misleading integration test.\\n    70→\\n    71→- **[testenv.go / remote_operations_test.go] Lint violations will block CI.** Running `golangci-lint run --new-from-rev=main` produces 19 issues in the new code:\\n    72→  - **`noctx` (14 in testenv.go, 4 in test file):** `exec.Command` without context. While existing code in testenv.go has the same pattern, these are *new* lines that CI's `golangci-lint-action@v9` will flag on a PR (it defaults to `only-new-issues: true`). The fix is to accept a `context.Context` parameter or use `exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), ...)`.\\n    73→  - **`unparam` (2):** `sessionID` return value in `createCheckpointedCommit` is never used; `branchName` parameter in `fileExistsOnRemoteBranch` always receives `paths.MetadataBranchName`. Either use or remove the unused return/parameter.\\n    74→  - **`wrapcheck` (1 in testenv.go:1826):** `RunPrePushWithError` returns an unwrapped error from `cmd.CombinedOutput()`. Since `testenv.go` is not a `_test.go` file, the `wrapcheck` exclusion for test files does not apply. Wrap the error with `fmt.Errorf`.\\n    75→\\n    76→### Suggestions (Consider)\\n    77→\\n    78→- **[remote_operations_test.go:230-236] Trails assertion in `TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints` is still conditional.** If the trails branch is never created locally, the test logs a message and passes without verifying trails behavior. This makes the test weaker than the requirements demand (\\\"entire/trails/v1 IS on remote\\\"). Consider using the same `createOrphanBranch` approach from `TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent` to guarantee the branch exists.\\n    79→\\n    80→- **[remote_operations_test.go:324-374] `TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin` relies on URL parse failure, not fork detection.** The test configures `checkpoint_remote` with `different-org/checkpoints`, but since origin is a local file path, `parseGitRemoteURL` fails before fork detection logic runs. The test comment (line 330-337) acknowledges this and references a unit test in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`. This is an acceptable approach -- the test verifies the integration behavior (\\\"checkpoints still land on origin when checkpoint URL derivation fails\\\"). Consider renaming the test to `REDACTED` to more accurately describe what it actually tests.\\n    81→\\n    82→- **[remote_operations_test.go:384] `createCheckpointedCommit` could return only `checkpointID`.** Since `sessionID` is never used at any call site, removing it simplifies the API and fixes the `unparam` lint issue simultaneously.\\n    83→\\n    84→- **[testenv.go:1780] `PatchSettings` writes with 0o644 permissions.** The `gosec` linter flags this as G306 (expects 0600 or less for WriteFile). Settings files likely don't contain secrets in tests, but changing to 0o600 silences the warning at no cost.\\n    85→\\n    86→- **[remote_operations_test.go:696-743] `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent` could assert more.** The test verifies that session start and PrePush don't error, but doesn't verify that the session actually _works_ (e.g., checkpoint is created locally, data can be read). Adding a `cloneEnv.BranchExists(paths.MetadataBranchName)` assertion after the commit would strengthen the test.\\n    87→\\n    88→### Praise\\n    89→\\n    90→- Excellent fix for the `runPrePushInDir` issue -- `RunPrePush` and `RunPrePushWithError` on TestEnv are clean, consistent with the rest of the infrastructure, and provide both fatal-on-error and return-error variants.\\n    91→- The `createCheckpointedCommit` helper significantly reduces boilerplate. Tests are now shorter and the important parts (setup, assertions) are more prominent.\\n    92→- `GetBranchTipParentCount` is a well-designed helper that correctly validates the merge commit structure in the concurrent push test.\\n    93→- Good documentation in test comments explaining design tradeoffs (e.g., why `FetchMetadataBranch` is used instead of `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`, why checkpoint_remote routing is tested at a lower level).\\n    94→- The `createOrphanBranch` helper is implemented correctly using go-git plumbing APIs instead of switching the working tree (which would conflict with parallel tests).\\n    95→- `FetchMetadataBranch` on TestEnv (replacing the standalone helper) properly fatals on error, making test failures easier to diagnose.\\n    96→- All 13 tests pass, run in parallel, and complete in ~12 seconds total.\\n    97→- Good coverage progression: from 7 tests in review-01 to 13 tests now.\\n    98→\\n    99→## Summary\\n   100→\\n   101→**Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES**\\n   102→\\n   103→Significant progress since review-01. The critical `runPrePushInDir` issue is fully fixed. The test boilerplate reduction, merge commit verification, and trails branch test restructuring are all well done. New tests were added for checkpoint_remote routing, fork detection fallback, and clone with unreachable checkpoint remote.\\n   104→\\n   105→However, two important issues remain:\\n   106→\\n   107→1. **The graceful degradation test (review-01 Critical #2) is still not testing the production graceful degradation code path.** The test has been restructured to show a git push failing to a non-existent path, but the push is done by test code, not by `doPushBranch`. The production code's error handling (catch push failure, warn, return nil) is not exercised. This was the same fundamental problem flagged in review-01.\\n   108→\\n   109→2. **Lint violations will block CI.** The 19 new lint issues (noctx, unparam, wrapcheck) need to be addressed before the PR can pass CI checks. These are straightforward fixes.\\n   110→\\n   111→3. **The checkpoint_remote routing test bypasses production code.** While it verifies the data routing concept, it uses raw `git push` rather than `pushBranchIfNeeded` or `PrePush`. This should at minimum be documented clearly as a \\\"data integrity\\\" test, not a \\\"routing logic\\\" test.\\n   112→\\n   113→**Estimated effort to address:**\\n   114→- Lint fixes: ~30 minutes (mechanical changes: add `context.Background()`, remove unused return, wrap error, fix permissions)\\n   115→- Graceful degradation test: ~1 hour (either restructure to test `doPushBranch` directly with a bad URL-like target, or document why integration-level testing is not feasible and rely on unit tests)\\n   116→- Checkpoint remote routing documentation: ~15 minutes (clarify in comments what is and isn't being tested)\\n   117→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"d4a63b7f-feb7-4bb1-8ec5-44a022de597d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:46.039Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"c98f12e6-1567-4d08-9793-9730507b58d2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:46.059Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c98f12e6-1567-4d08-9793-9730507b58d2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T16:14:52.709Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_013PJvm7boLUernc21n8UtQg\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015WdB8rFCaU7Mnbrqqu9Czc\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/remote_operations_test.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":7878,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":19125,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":7878,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3GdLfVUUAWgGQuVbLh9\",\"uuid\":\"fe4fd397-9ced-4b1b-9b5a-7111bc1f1057\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"p