ntext_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3MJsXRrkYyVR7tJEgay\",\"uuid\":\"d0cd31ef-e9c3-4622-8992-93d27fec3fa4\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"5503d6d6-d72b-459c-a17c-e470ca70ca1f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T17:16:13.397Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5503d6d6-d72b-459c-a17c-e470ca70ca1f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01BdpoZGdEs1X6HSiGrmBKt5\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Remote Operations Tests -- Summary\\n     2→\\n     3→## What Was Implemented\\n     4→\\n     5→### Infrastructure helpers (testenv.go)\\n     6→\\n     7→Original infrastructure (from task-01):\\n     8→- `SetupBareRemote()` - creates a bare git repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD\\n     9→- `SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` - same with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n    10→- `CloneFrom(bareDir)` - clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new TestEnv with `.entire/` initialized\\n    11→- `BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` - checks branch existence on bare remote\\n    12→- `PatchSettings(extra)` - merges keys into `.entire/settings.json`\\n    13→- `GitPush(remote, refSpec)` - pushes a branch to remote\\n    14→- `GitFetch(remote, args...)` - fetches from remote\\n    15→\\n    16→New infrastructure (from review-01 fixes):\\n    17→- `RunPrePush(remote)` - runs pre-push hook via CLI binary with `env.cliEnv()` (replaces standalone `runPrePushInDir`)\\n    18→- `RunPrePushWithError(remote)` - same but returns error\\n    19→- `FetchMetadataBranch(remoteURL)` - fetches metadata branch with `t.Fatalf` on error\\n    20→- `GetBranchTipParentCount(branchName)` - returns parent count for branch tip commit\\n    21→\\n    22→### P0 Tests -- PrePush Basic Flow (4 tests)\\n    23→1. **TestPrePush_PushesCheckpointBranchToOrigin** - session + condense + PrePush verifies `entire/checkpoints/v1` arrives on bare remote with checkpoint metadata\\n    24→2. **TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent** - creates trails branch if not present, verifies push mechanism works\\n    25→3. **TestPrePush_NoOpWhenNoCheckpoints** - no session activity => PrePush succeeds silently, no branches on remote\\n    26→4. **TestPrePush_IdempotentWhenAlreadyPushed** - push twice, remote ref unchanged on second push\\n    27→\\n    28→### P0 Tests -- Checkpoint Remote Config (3 tests)\\n    29→5. **TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints** - `push_sessions: false` => checkpoints NOT on remote, trails still pushed\\n    30→6. **TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote** - two bare remotes, checkpoints to checkpoint remote, trails to origin\\n    31→7. **TestPrePush_ForkDetectionFallsBackToOrigin** - different owner in checkpoint_remote, checkpoints fall back to origin\\n    32→\\n    33→### P0 Tests -- Clone and Resume (4 tests)\\n    34→8. **TestCloneAndResume_FetchesCheckpointMetadata** - push, clone, fetch metadata branch, verify data present\\n    35→9. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionListingWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, verify checkpoint IDs discoverable\\n    36→10. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionLogRetrievalWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, read transcript content\\n    37→11. **TestCloneAndResume_NewSessionPushAppends** - push from A, clone as B, new session + push => remote has both\\n    38→\\n    39→### P1 Tests -- Non-Fast-Forward Recovery (1 test)\\n    40→12. **TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries** - two clones push concurrently; verifies merge commit with 2 parents\\n    41→\\n    42→### P1 Tests -- Graceful Degradation (2 tests)\\n    43→13. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues** - unreachable checkpoint remote does not fail push, trails still arrive on origin\\n    44→14. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent** - clone + unreachable checkpoint_remote, session starts cleanly\\n    45→\\n    46→### Helper Functions\\n    47→- `createCheckpointedCommit` - reduces 8+ lines of boilerplate per session setup to one call\\n    48→- `createOrphanBranch` - creates orphan branches via go-git plumbing (no working tree switch)\\n    49→- `pushBranchToTarget` / `pushBranchToTargetWithError` - direct `git push` to arbitrary targets\\n    50→\\n    51→## Review-01 Issues Addressed\\n    52→\\n    53→### Critical (2/2 fixed)\\n    54→1. **`runPrePushInDir` uses wrong env pattern** -- Replaced with `env.RunPrePush(remote)` method using `env.cliEnv()`\\n    55→2. **Graceful degradation test doesn't test degradation** -- Now configures unreachable checkpoint remote and verifies trails still push to origin\\n    56→\\n    57→### Important (4/4 fixed)\\n    58→3. **Trails push test doesn't verify trails were actually pushed** -- Creates trails branch if missing, then asserts it arrives on remote\\n    59→4. **`push_sessions: false` test doesn't verify trails ARE still pushed** -- Added assertion for trails on remote\\n    60→5. **Clone-and-resume tests bypass production `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`** -- Added clear documentation explaining why (CWD-based `OpenRepository` incompatible with `t.Parallel`), cross-referenced production function unit tests, replaced silent error swallowing with `t.Fatalf`\\n    61→6. **Concurrent push test doesn't verify merge commit has two parents** -- Added `GetBranchTipParentCount` method and assertion\\n    62→\\n    63→### Coverage Gaps (5/8 addressed)\\n    64→7a. **checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote** -- Implemented at pushBranchIfNeeded level\\n    65→7b. **fork detection falls back to origin** -- Implemented with checkpoint_remote config + local path fallback\\n    66→8a. **Unreachable checkpoint remote on clone (fetch is silent)** -- Implemented\\n    67→8b. **Disconnected metadata recovery during concurrent push** -- Deferred (requires empty-orphan bug artifact setup)\\n    68→8c. **Fetch timeout test** -- Deferred (P2, requires slow remote simulation)\\n    69→\\n    70→## Design Decisions\\n    71→\\n    72→1. **Trails branch creation**: Trails are only created via \\\"trail start\\\", not by basic session+commit. Tests that need trails create a minimal orphan branch using go-git plumbing APIs (avoids working tree conflicts).\\n    73→\\n    74→2. **Checkpoint remote routing with local paths**: `resolvePushSettings` derives URLs from origin's SSH/HTTPS protocol. Local path remotes can't be parsed as URLs. The routing test operates at the `pushBranchIfNeeded`/`git push` level. URL derivation is covered by unit tests in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`.\\n    75→\\n    76→3. **Clone tests vs `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`**: The production function uses `OpenRepository` (CWD-based), incompatible with `t.Parallel()`. Clone tests use raw `git fetch` via `env.FetchMetadataBranch` and document this clearly. Production code path covered by dedicated unit tests.\\n    77→\\n    78→4. **`createCheckpointedCommit` helper**: Reduces the repeated 8-line session setup pattern to a single call, making test intent clearer.\\n    79→\\n    80→## Verification\\n    81→\\n    82→- `mise run fmt` -- clean\\n    83→- `mise run lint` -- 0 issues\\n    84→- `mise run test:ci` -- all tests pass (unit + integration + 43/43 E2E canary)\\n    85→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"96cccd5c-07fa-4059-bc4b-12533226b492\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T17:16:13.405Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"cd441d52-08f9-4a5d-8ac0-dcee84b6edc7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T17:16:13.452Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cd441d52-08f9-4a5d-8ac0-dcee84b6edc7\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T17:16:51.326Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PySVvRPzVDkQtFRC6M63Qm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Rmb4ji4KVAvW3V7vhs75d8\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1/docs/requirements/remote-operations-tests/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Remote Operations Tests -- Summary\\n\\n## What Was Implemented\\n\\n### Infrastructure helpers (testenv.go)\\n\\nOriginal infrastructure (from task-01):\\n- `SetupBareRemote()` - creates a bare git repo, adds as \\\"origin\\\", pushes HEAD\\n- `SetupNamedBareRemote(name)` - same with custom remote name (for checkpoint_remote scenarios)\\n- `CloneFrom(bareDir)` - clones bare repo into new temp dir, returns new TestEnv with `.entire/` initialized\\n- `BranchExistsOnRemote(bareDir, branch)` - checks branch existence on bare remote\\n- `PatchSettings(extra)` - merges keys into `.entire/settings.json`\\n- `GitPush(remote, refSpec)` - pushes a branch to remote\\n- `GitFetch(remote, args...)` - fetches from remote\\n\\nNew infrastructure (from review-01 fixes):\\n- `RunPrePush(remote)` - runs pre-push hook via CLI binary with `env.cliEnv()` (replaces standalone `runPrePushInDir`)\\n- `RunPrePushWithError(remote)` - same but returns error (wraps with `fmt.Errorf`)\\n- `FetchMetadataBranch(remoteURL)` - fetches metadata branch with `t.Fatalf` on error\\n- `GetBranchTipParentCount(branchName)` - returns parent count for branch tip commit\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- PrePush Basic Flow (4 tests)\\n1. **TestPrePush_PushesCheckpointBranchToOrigin** - session + condense + PrePush verifies `entire/checkpoints/v1` arrives on bare remote with checkpoint metadata\\n2. **TestPrePush_PushesTrailsBranchWhenPresent** - creates trails branch if not present, verifies push mechanism works\\n3. **TestPrePush_NoOpWhenNoCheckpoints** - no session activity => PrePush succeeds silently, no branches on remote\\n4. **TestPrePush_IdempotentWhenAlreadyPushed** - push twice, remote ref unchanged on second push\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- Checkpoint Remote Config (3 tests)\\n5. **TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints** - `push_sessions: false` => checkpoints NOT on remote, trails guaranteed present and pushed\\n6. **TestPrePush_CheckpointRemoteRoutesToSeparateRemote** - data routing verification with two bare remotes, checkpoints to checkpoint remote, trails to origin\\n7. **REDACTED** - checkpoint_remote configured but origin is local path, checkpoints fall back to origin\\n\\n### P0 Tests -- Clone and Resume (4 tests)\\n8. **TestCloneAndResume_FetchesCheckpointMetadata** - push, clone, fetch metadata branch, verify data present\\n9. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionListingWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, verify checkpoint IDs discoverable\\n10. **TestCloneAndResume_SessionLogRetrievalWorksAfterClone** - clone + fetch, read transcript content\\n11. **TestCloneAndResume_NewSessionPushAppends** - push from A, clone as B, new session + push => remote has both\\n\\n### P1 Tests -- Non-Fast-Forward Recovery (1 test)\\n12. **TestConcurrentPush_SecondPusherMergesAndRetries** - two clones push concurrently; verifies merge commit with 2 parents\\n\\n### P1 Tests -- Graceful Degradation (2 tests)\\n13. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemotePushContinues** - checkpoint_remote configured, URL derivation fails with local path, fallback to origin, trails also on origin\\n14. **TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent** - clone + unreachable checkpoint_remote, session starts cleanly, verifies local checkpoint created\\n\\n### Unit Tests -- push_common_test.go (3 new tests)\\n15. **TestDoPushBranch_UnreachableTarget_ReturnsNil** - exercises `doPushBranch` directly with non-existent path, verifies graceful degradation (returns nil, not error)\\n16. **TestPushBranchIfNeeded_UnreachableTarget_ReturnsNil** - exercises full `pushBranchIfNeeded` path with unreachable target\\n17. **TestPushBranchIfNeeded_LocalBareRepo_PushesSuccessfully** - exercises `pushBranchIfNeeded` with local bare repo as target, verifying the core routing mechanism works\\n\\n### Helper Functions\\n- `createCheckpointedCommit` - reduces 8+ lines of boilerplate per session setup to one call (returns only checkpointID)\\n- `ensureTrailsBranchExists` - creates orphan trails branch if not already present\\n- `createOrphanBranch` - creates orphan branches via go-git plumbing (no working tree switch)\\n- `pushBranchToTarget` / `pushBranchToTargetWithError` - direct `git push` to arbitrary targets\\n\\n## Review-01 Issues Addressed\\n\\n### Critical (2/2 fixed)\\n1. **`runPrePushInDir` uses wrong env pattern** -- Replaced with `env.RunPrePush(remote)` method using `env.cliEnv()`\\n2. **Graceful degradation test doesn't test degradation** -- Now configures unreachable checkpoint remote and verifies trails still push to origin\\n\\n### Important (4/4 fixed)\\n3. **Trails push test doesn't verify trails were actually pushed** -- Creates trails branch if missing, then asserts it arrives on remote\\n4. **`push_sessions: false` test doesn't verify trails ARE still pushed** -- Added assertion for trails on remote\\n5. **Clone-and-resume tests bypass production `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`** -- Added clear documentation explaining why (CWD-based `OpenRepository` incompatible with `t.Parallel`), cross-referenced production function unit tests, replaced silent error swallowing with `t.Fatalf`\\n6. **Concurrent push test doesn't verify merge commit has two parents** -- Added `GetBranchTipParentCount` method and assertion\\n\\n### Coverage Gaps (5/8 addressed)\\n7a. **checkpoint_remote routes checkpoints to separate remote** -- Implemented at pushBranchIfNeeded level\\n7b. **fork detection falls back to origin** -- Renamed to CheckpointURLDerivationFailure, documented accurately\\n8a. **Unreachable checkpoint remote on clone (fetch is silent)** -- Implemented\\n8b. **Disconnected metadata recovery during concurrent push** -- Deferred (requires empty-orphan bug artifact setup)\\n8c. **Fetch timeout test** -- Deferred (P2, requires slow remote simulation)\\n\\n## Review-02 Issues Addressed\\n\\n### Important (3/3 fixed)\\n\\n1. **Lint violations (19 total, CI-blocking)** -- All 19 issues fixed:\\n   - `noctx` (14 in testenv.go, 4 in test file): replaced `exec.Command` with `exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), ...)`\\n   - `unparam` (2): removed unused `sessionID` return from `createCheckpointedCommit`; removed always-same `branchName` param from `fileExistsOnRemoteBranch`\\n   - `wrapcheck` (1): wrapped error in `RunPrePushWithError` with `fmt.Errorf`\\n   - `gosec` G306: changed permissions from `0o644` to `0o600` in `PatchSettings`\\n   - `gosec` G304: added nolint comment for `ReadFile` in `PatchSettings` (path from test env, not user input)\\n\\n2. **Graceful degradation test bypasses production code** -- Restructured:\\n   - Added 2 unit tests in `push_common_test.go` that directly exercise `doPushBranch` and `pushBranchIfNeeded` with non-existent paths, verifying the core graceful degradation behavior (returns nil, not error)\\n   - Added 1 unit test for `pushBranchIfNeeded` with a valid local bare repo, verifying the routing mechanism works\\n   - Integration test now configures checkpoint_remote and runs full PrePush, verifying the resolvePushSettings -> fallback path\\n   - Clear documentation cross-referencing unit tests for the actual doPushBranch error handling\\n\\n3. **Checkpoint remote routing test bypasses PrePush** -- Improved documentation:\\n   - Added detailed comments explaining WHY the test operates at the git push level (local file paths cannot be parsed by `resolvePushSettings`)\\n   - Cross-referenced unit tests for URL derivation (`checkpoint_remote_test.go`) and routing (`push_common_test.go`)\\n   - Described as \\\"data routing verification test\\\" to set clear expectations\\n\\n### Suggestions addressed\\n\\n- **Trails assertion in `TestPrePush_PushDisabledSkipsCheckpoints` now unconditional** -- Uses `ensureTrailsBranchExists` helper to guarantee the branch exists before asserting\\n- **Fork detection test renamed** -- Now `REDACTED` to accurately describe the local-path-can't-be-parsed behavior\\n- **`createCheckpointedCommit` simplified** -- Returns only `checkpointID` (removed unused `sessionID`)\\n- **Clone test asserts more** -- `TestGracefulDegradation_UnreachableCheckpointRemoteOnCloneIsSilent` now verifies local checkpoint branch exists after commit\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **Trails branch creation**: Trails are only created via \\\"trail start\\\", not by basic session+commit. Tests that need trails use `ensureTrailsBranchExists` which creates a minimal orphan branch using go-git plumbing APIs (avoids working tree conflicts).\\n\\n2. **Checkpoint remote routing with local paths**: `resolvePushSettings` derives URLs from origin's SSH/HTTPS protocol. Local path remotes can't be parsed as URLs. The routing test operates at the `git push` level for data verification. The production `pushBranchIfNeeded` function (which PrePush calls) is covered by unit tests in `push_common_test.go`. URL derivation is covered by unit tests in `checkpoint_remote_test.go`.\\n\\n3. **Graceful degradation testing**: The production `doPushBranch` graceful degradation (catches push failure, returns nil) cannot be triggered through `PrePush` with local path remotes because `resolvePushSettings` falls back before reaching `doPushBranch`. Unit tests in `push_common_test.go` exercise this path directly. The integration test verifies the fallback-to-origin behavior.\\n\\n4. **Clone tests vs `fetchMetadataBranchIfMissing`**: The production function uses `OpenRepository` (CWD-based), incompatible with `t.Parallel()`. Clone tests use raw `git fetch` via `env.FetchMetadataBranch` and document this clearly. Production code path covered by dedicated unit tests.\\n\\n5. **`createCheckpointedCommit` helper**: Reduces the repeated 8-line session setup pattern to a single call, making test intent clearer.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- `mise run fmt` -- clean\\n- `mise run lint` -- 0 issues\\n- `golangci-lint run --new-from-rev=main --build-tags=integration` -- 0 issues\\n- `mise run test` -- all unit tests pass\\n- `mise run test:integration` -- all 14 integration tests pass\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2127,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":126550,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":2127,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":25,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ3MK9uv3etcQw4U7ZwhE\",\"uuid\":\"cc7f36b1-7c6f-4899-8bf6-8fbc77fb4ddb\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a18b4ff6f715c8372\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017Mk8s2a8UbTpKm61XPz5RD\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019KN7wWBLJ8QF9o4eQGVHbb\",\"uuid\":\"74534451-b064-4bb5-b785-d8f2fcdb40e2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T17:16:51.326Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_worktree1\",\"sessionId\":\"36636388-6a2e-45ad-ac63-5d08a06fbf23\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"feature/remote-operations-tests\",\"slug\":\"dazzling-moseying-otter\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"74534451-b064-4bb5-b785-d8f2fcdb40e2\",\"isSidechain